title: mex eggs
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix eggs and milk and beat slightly.
Add corn.
Place tortillas in bottom of greased dish. Pour egg mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: favorite buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine buttermilk and soda; add to dry ingredients, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface; knead lightly 10 to 12 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2 3/4-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 10 biscuits.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Cook onion and broccoli in butter until tender.
Add soup and cheese.
Heat very slowly.
Serve hot with Fritos, chips, etc.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and chopped onion until tender in a small amount of water. Drain. Mix with sour cream and half of the margarine, cheese and crackers. Pour in a buttered baking dish. Put the remaining crackers, margarine and cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: holiday meatballs
directions: Meatballs:
Mix onions, celery, garlic, chopped green onion tops, bread crumbs, chili powder, thyme and paprika to ground meat.
Add eggs and mix well.
Form into bite-size balls.
Bake in oven at 350° until brown.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter, add cocoa. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Pour into a greased 9-in. pie pan. Bake 30 minutes. Good served hot with ice cream and hot fudge.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and sour cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour, soda and vanilla.
Bake in loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Combine Crisco, sugar, vanilla and water.
Beat until creamy.
Add egg and flour mixture.
Fold in nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased pan.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy lasagna(try this, it really works!)
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, basil, oregano and 1 cup Parmesan cheese.
Set aside.
Spray pan with Pam. Line pan with raw (uncooked) lasagna noodles.
Cover with 1 cup spaghetti sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Put small amounts of ground beef or Italian sausage (take out of skin) evenly over top.
Put another layer of uncooked lasagna noodles over this.
Press down. Spoon cheese mixture over this.
Put Mozzarella cheese over this. Pour 1 cup sauce over this.
Pour 1/2 cup water over this also.

title: chess pie
directions: Sift together the sugar, flour and salt.
Set aside.
Cook in double boiler the cheese, butter and milk.
Add eggs when cool enough so not to set the eggs.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie crust and cook 1 hour at 325° or until done with toothpick test.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese, salt, pepper and eggs. Mix crabmeat, shrimp, margarine, mushrooms, cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, garlic, parsley, scallops, crab, onion, mushroom soup, Cheddar cheese and white wine.

Spray 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Coat bottom well. Layer noodles, cottage cheese mixture and crabmeat mixture and repeat. Top with Mozzarella cheese and paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let sit 15 minutes before serving.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar gradually.
Add egg whites; blend well.
Sift flour with salt.
Combine buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk mixture alternately to sugar mixture. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° until done (about 35 minutes in 9 x 12-inch pan).

title: uncooked cocoa cookies
directions: Boil butter or margarine, milk and sugar one minute in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients to hot mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper to cool.
Quick candy-like cookie treat recipe.
Fun for kids to make!

title: hamburger cookies
directions: Divide vanilla frosting.
Spread half of the wafers with frosting (flat side).
Sprinkle coconut on frosted wafers.
Lay peppermint patty on coconut.
With yellow coloring, tint rest of frosting.
Spread rest of wafers with frosting and lay on patty. Lightly brush tops with honey; sprinkle with sesame seed.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: corn scallop
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs until light. Add sugar, salt, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon, oil, water, flour and pumpkin. Beat with electric beater until well mixed. Stir in raisins and nuts. Grease a little four (1 pound) coffee cans. Fill half full. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done. Test as for cake. Let set in cans until cool. Turn upside down and remove from cans. They are just as good after freezing as fresh.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party sandwich filling
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes 2 1/3 cups filling.

title: meatball cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar, eggs and milk, then 1 cup chopped nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls, dip fingers in Crisco to roll. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Brown bottom. Frost when cool.
Makes over 100.
Divide recipe in half, if desired.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Stir the butter or margarine, sugar and evaporated milk together in a 3-quart bowl.
Microwave on High for 11 minutes (sugar should be completely dissolved).
Immediately add the chocolate bits; stir until melted.
Beat in (with mixer) the Marshmallow Fluff and vanilla.
Fold in the chopped walnuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut when cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour in baking dish or pan.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pork chop and potato scallop
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Blend in soup, sour cream, water and parsley.
In a 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes seasoned with salt and pepper and topped with mushroom sauce. Place chops over all.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for about 1 1/4 hours.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mimi's jello salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with all the other ingredients.
Put in refrigerator several hours to chill.

title: no egg ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Freeze in an electric churn.

title: casserole ala mexico
directions: Layer ingredients in the order listed in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serves 4.

title: chow chow relish
directions: Combine chopped vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 4 to 6 hours in a cool place.
Drain well.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices; simmer 10 minutes.
Add vegetables; simmer 10 more minutes.
Bring to a boil.
Pack boiling hot in sterilized jars, leaving 1/8-inch at top.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar and cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla, peanut butter and marshmallow.
When melted, add peanuts (chopped), then beat in confectioners sugar.
Mix until hard to stir and confectioners sugar doesn't blend in anymore.
Put in a pan and spread with a spoon.
Chill until firm, then cut into squares.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix butter, salt, pepper, onion, soup, milk, sour cream and cheese.
Add potatoes and place in two 2-quart casserole dishes. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Buttered crumbs on top are optional.

title: copper pennies
directions: Clean and cut carrots into bite-size circles.
Cook until tender.
Chop half the onion and bell pepper.
Cut remaining half into ringlets to decorate top.
Drain carrots.
Mix soup, sugar, vinegar, oil, mustard and Worcestershire sauce until blended together.
Pour over carrot, onion and pepper mixture.
Place ringlets on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: green beans and parsley
directions: Clean and wash beans. Boil beans until tender, but still firm. Drain and cool beans. Toss beans with oil, vinegar, parsley, salt and pepper.
Serve cold.
May be refrigerated for 2 days.

title: million dollar pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice together.
Add other ingredients. Mix well.
Put into vanilla or chocolate wafer crust or graham cracker crust.
This makes 2 very rich pies.
Keep refrigerated. Eat one now or freeze both for later use.

title: spoon bread
directions: Add corn meal to boiling salted water.
Wait until thick and add butter.
Beat egg yolks.
Add to milk, then stir into corn meal.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and baking powder.
Bake in buttered dish at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie plate 3/4 full with sliced apples.
Sprinkle over 1 tablespoon sugar and the cinnamon.
Melt butter or margarine. Add 1 cup sugar, flour, egg and nuts (optional).
Mix well.
It will be thick.
Pour over apples and bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: parsnip puree
directions: In casserole dish, combine parsnips and water.
Microwave, covered, on High for 5 to 7 minutes or until tender; drain well.

title: peach jello
directions: Mix peach Jell-O and crushed pineapple.
Stir into Jell-O mixture the buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Put in serving dish and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: pumpkin cranberry bread
directions: Combine flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Combine eggs, sugar, pumpkin and oil in small mixer bowl; beat just until blended.
Add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.
Fold in cranberries.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 5 to 10 minutes; remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: fillets of perch dijonnaise
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute onions in butter until soft.
Add mushrooms and stir over high heat 2 minutes.
Stir in sherry, mustard, herbs and seasonings.
Sprinkle 1/2 of crumbs in greased 7 1/2 x 11 3/4-inch baking dish.
Arrange fish over crumbs in single layer.
Spread mushroom mixture over fish.
Sprinkle on remaining crumbs and cover with cheese.
Bake about 25 minutes.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Place ice cubes and milk in electric blender and whirl for 1 minute until smooth.
Add banana, vanilla and sugar; whirl until foamy.
Makes 1 serving.

title: gazpacho
directions: Beat together the oil and lemon juice.
Stir in the tomato juice, broth, onion, tomatoes, celery, Tabasco, salt and pepper. Taste for seasoning.
The mixture should be well seasoned.
(It may require more salt or Tabasco, depending on individual taste.) Chill the soup at least 3 hours.
Pour into a tureen.
Serve the green peppers, cucumbers and croutons separately to be passed and added to each serving.
The soup will keep several days in the refrigerator.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 1/4's.
Shake a few biscuits at a time in a bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Place around in tube pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs somewhat, not extensively.
Add sugar and Karo. Heat liquid in double boiler until ingredients are well-blended (hot, but not very hot).
Add butter or margarine and remove from heat.
Allow liquid to cool.
Add vanilla.
Pour chopped nuts in pie shell and add cooled liquid filling.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: grandma watt's corn pudd'n
directions: Beat eggs until blended.
Add all of the ingredients and stir until nicely mixed.
Pour in a Pyrex bowl and bake at 350° until mixture is golden brown and holds together, approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Crush crackers and melt 1 stick of butter.
Mix together. Cook broccoli by directions on package.
While cooking, cut cheese and other stick of butter into cubes.
Drain broccoli and add cubed cheese and butter to broccoli.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan with butter.
Put broccoli mixture on bottom of pan and crushed cracker mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.
Enjoy!

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly and pat dry.
Place flour, paprika, and pepper in plastic food bag and shake.
Place pieces of chicken in bag and shake, coating each piece of chicken with flour mixture.
Pour olive oil in baking dish and lay chicken in pan. Bake, uncovered, in oven at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake for 15 minutes longer, until tender.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Make crumbs of dry ingredients and shortening.
Add beaten egg, water and vinegar.
Can be stored in refrigerator.
Makes 3 or 4 double crust pies.

title: buttercream decorating icing
directions: Cream the butter and shortening together with mixer. Add vanilla and salt.
Beat in the sugar, one cup at a time, blending well. Add milk and beat at high speed until light and fluffy. Keep icing covered in the refrigerator when not in use.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: mom's easy dinner
directions: In electric skillet, melt butter.
Place sliced potatoes in pan. Add green pepper, onion, salt, pepper, garlic powder, cabbage and/or sauerkraut. Cook for 1/2 hour with lid on, stirring regularly, at 300°.
Remove lid.
Place sliced kielbasa or smoked sausage on top. Cook without lid until potatoes brown.

title: banana peach bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; beat at low speed until blended.
Beat at medium 3 more minutes. Spoon into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Loosen sides, remove and cool on rack.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples and lay in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and egg with fork until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Melt butter and drizzle over topping. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fish fillets with crabmeat stuffing topped with cream sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except fillets, in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until fish begins to flake.
Remove and let stand 5 minutes covered.

Place fillets on a buttered baking sheet; top each with a generous scoop of stuffing dotted with margarine. Place under broiler in your regular oven about 6-inches below heat; broil until stuffing is lightly browned.
Place on a heated serving dish and top with Cream Sauce.
Garnish with lemon slice and sprig of parsley.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients coarsely and set 1 cup aside.
To remaining mixture, add milk, vanilla, salt and baking soda.
Mix and put in pan.

title: barbecue roast beef sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until celery is done.
Mix with beef.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream. Spread on round tray or pan about 12-inches in diameter. Next, spread jar of taco sauce, then cover with shredded Cheddar cheese. Sprinkle on chopped tomato and green pepper and garnish with chopped green onion. Serve with nacho chips.

title: onion casserole
directions: Peel and boil onions until done; drain and put in a casserole.
(This can be done day before; refrigerate.)
Make enough medium white sauce to cover onions.
Stir into sauce 1 cup Velveeta cheese; stir until melted.
Pour over onions.
Crumble enough Ritz crackers to cover top.
Drizzle melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until bubbly around edges.

title: plain pastry crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening and water until mealy.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Lay loosely in pie pan and press to sides.
Build up on edges.
Prick all over and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: pasta with eggplant sauce
directions: Peel and dice onion.
Seed bell peppers and cut into 1/2-inch squares.
Pare eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and peppers and stir to coat with oil.
Add eggplant and tomatoes.
Cook, stirring frequently, over very high heat until starting to brown (about 5 minutes).
Crush garlic with tines of fork and add to sauce. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, over medium heat 4 to 5 minutes.
Add basil and remove from heat.
Cook and drain pasta (ziti) well and add eggplant sauce.
Mix and serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put into unbaked pie shell.
Pour half and half over dry mixture.
Stir and mix together with fingers, being careful not to tear pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 90 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: chile verde con carne
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch pieces and brown in oil.
Add chopped jalapenos, chilies and onions; cook until tender.
Add flour and brown a bit.
Add tomatoes, garlic, cumin, salt, pepper and water. Bring to a boil.
Let simmer until meat is tender.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat sugar, butter, eggs, vinegar and vanilla together, then add coconut, raisins and nuts.
Mix well and pour into a 9-inch unbaked, deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes. Check periodically as ovens vary.

title: wagon wheel cookies(sugar cookies)
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream margarine and sugar. Beat the egg and milk.
Add dry ingredients to liquid ingredients. Roll out on lightly floured board.
Cut with a cookie cutter.
Bake at 375°, 15 minutes (8 to 10 minutes for soft, chewy cookies). Makes 4 dozen.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
(Can mix right in 9 x 13-inch pan.) Top with grated cheese.
Can refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in moderate oven for 1 hour in a greased and floured loaf pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients EXCEPT 1 cup chow mein noodles. Pour mixture into a greased casserole.
Sprinkle the cup of chow mein noodles on the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or if needed a little longer uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: pizza doggies
directions: Cook garlic in oil until lightly browned. Add soup, water, parsley and oregano. Cook over low heat for 15 minutes. Stir often. Place hot dogs on buns in large shallow baking pan. Fill hot dogs with sauce. Top with cheese. Place under broiler for about 1 minute or until cheese melts.

title: vanilla ice cream(no eggs)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.
This keeps well in freezer.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Use
fresh green cucumbers.
Wash.
Remove stem end and slice 1/4-inch
thick.
Put into an enamelware or glass bowl. Sprinkle with
salt	and
add
water.
Cover and let stand 24 hours.
Turn into
a colander and drain well.
Put into large enamelware
pot; add
onions
(sliced
1/8-inch
thick), then vinegar,
sugar
and spices.
Stir to mix well.	Heat to boiling, then simmer 3 to 4 minutes.

title: banana-lemon tea bread
directions: In a large bowl, cream shortening with sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in bananas and lemon juice.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt. Blend into banana mixture; stir in lemon peel.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake isn't gooey inside (test with a toothpick).
Remove from pan and cool.
Sift powdered sugar over top, if desired, before serving.

title: tirami su
directions: Mix coffee, brandy and confectioners sugar.
Brush over pound cake.
Place in goblets.
Mix Ricotta and chocolate chips and spoon over cake.
Serves 4.

title: chicken pot pies
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place Pillsbury pie crust bottom in Corning Ware pot and put aside.
Saute butter and chopped onion. Add flour and seasonings until soft.
Add broth and milk until sauce thickens.
Take off heat.
Put potatoes in microwave bowl and heat until potatoes are soft.
Add potatoes and chicken into sauce.
Put on low on stove until chicken is done.
Add frozen vegetables.
Pour mixture into a Pillsbury pie crust.
Put pie crust lid on.
Bake in a 425° oven for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry pineapple mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold liquid (pineapple juice and water).
Stir in light sour cream. Add remaining ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9-inch or 15 x 9-inch glass dish.
Refrigerate and serve when set up.

title: szechwan shrimp
directions: Combine in a bowl.

title: lillie bean's persimmon cookies
directions: Cream egg and butter; add sugar.
Add flour, nuts, raisins and spices.
Beat egg; add to persimmon pulp.
Dissolve soda in persimmon pulp.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt, flour and cornstarch.
Add this mixture to slightly beaten egg yolks.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until it just begins to thicken.
Add rice, raisins and vanilla.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Place in pan containing about 1-inch boiling water.
Bake in oven at 325° until brown.

title: turkey crepes
directions: Beat flour, eggs, salt and milk until smooth.
In hot, lightly buttered crepe pan or equivalent, pour 2 tablespoons batter for each crepe.
Tilt pan to let batter flow under cooking crepe. Hold crepes in warm plate.

title: smoked brisket
directions: Mix all in a bowl.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil and pour mixture into pan.
Place the trimmed brisket and turn meat over in the sauce 2 or 3 times.
Then cover with foil and seal tightly. Bake at 250° for 5 1/2 hours.
Do not open oven door.
(Can be cooked overnight.)

title: bean pot
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan.
Saute chopped pepper and onion in bacon drippings.
Add ground chuck and brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Combine oil, garlic powder, dill and Ranch dressing in a jar. Shake well to mix.
Put crackers in container, pour oil mixture over crackers.
Put lid on container and shake well.
Let sit for at least 2 hours, shaking and stirring every half hour.
Store in airtight container.
Enjoy!

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in 2 cups of water until tender.
Add cheese. Allow to melt before adding the rest of the ingredients.
Add milk to the consistency that you want.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together biscuit mix, cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir in eggs, zucchini and onion until moistened.
Fry in hot skillet until brown on both sides.
Makes 12 patties.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove from bones and cut into small pieces.
Place in large baking dish.
Mix cream of chicken and cream of celery soups with 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Fold in mixed vegetables.
Pour over cut up chicken.
Mix self-rising flour, melted margarine and buttermilk together; spoon over chicken-soup mixture.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: branded pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients with rotary beater until smooth.
Grease griddle if necessary.
Drizzle batter from teaspoon onto hot griddle to form an initial (initials must be made backwards to make them appear right when pancakes are served).
When bottom side of initial is brown, pour about 1/4 cup batter over initial. Turn when bubbles appear.
Bake other side until golden brown. Makes about 18 pancakes.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Simmer first six ingredients until thick, stirring frequently. Add bacon, onion and pepper.
Serve immediately over spinach greens or sliced tomato.

title: great cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon and flatten on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine, sour cream and 2 eggs.
Mix in flour, baking powder and 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Spread 2/3 batter on bottom of cake pan.
Spread 1 can pie filling.
Spread rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: refrigerator date pinwheels
directions: Combine dates, sugar and water; cook until thick.
Mix in nuts and cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix.
Add flour, soda and salt, sifted together.
Mix well.
Roll out and spread with date mixture.
Roll as jelly roll and chill.
Slice off and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: cheese soup primavera
directions: Melt the butter in a soup pot.
Saute the onions, celery, and carrots.
Combine the chicken broth with half and half.
Stir the flour into the vegetables, mixing well.
Add the liquid and stir. Add the potato soup and broccoli.
Mix until smooth.
Gradually add small chunks of cheese, stirring continuously until cheese melts.
Keep warm until ready to serve.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Beat all of the ingredients together.
Line 9-inch pie dish with pastry.
Add enough sliced peaches to fill the dish.
Pour the mixture over the peaches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Very good with Cool Whip!

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Put one layer of the cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Cover with 1/2 can cherry pie filling, then 1 package vanilla pudding, 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 fruit cocktail, 1 package coconut.
Top with 1 carton Cool Whip and 1/2 pecans.
Repeat layers.
Garnish with Cool Whip and pecans.
May top with maraschino cherries if desired.
Serves a bunch of people.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: bertha's hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain excess grease.
Mix cream cheese, soup, milk, salt and catsup; add to meat mixture.
Put into casserole dish or pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with canned biscuits.
Put back into oven and bake approximately 15 to 20 minutes (until biscuits are done).

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Then mix brown sugar, coconut and chopped pecans.
Sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake at 360°.

title: squash casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, mix all ingredients together except crackers. When adding milk, add enough sweet milk to make 1 cup. Place crackers on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add juice, vinegar and salt; chill.
When starting to gell, add grated raw carrots and crushed pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaves with favorite dressing.

title: howard's honey mustard salad dressing
directions: Whisk first 2 ingredients together.
Blend honey and mustard. Adjust the seasoning to taste with last 2 ingredients.
May be used as salad dressing or as dipping sauce.
It is a great dip for veggies as well.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Boil water, sugar, cornstarch, and salt until thickened.
Add strawberry jello.
Stir in 1 1/2 quarts of fresh strawberries. Pour into 2 baked pie shells.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread 2 cartons sour cream over this.
Pour on remaining jello and chill until firm.

title: corn bread loaf
directions: Scald milk. Add margarine, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Add cool milk to yeast. Stir to blend. Stir in beaten eggs, flour and cornmeal. Beat 2 minutes. This will be a thick batter. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Let rise until double, about 1 hour. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Add brown sugar. Cook on low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add milk and continue to cook until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and gradually add powdered sugar slowly.
Stir and add vanilla.
Mix well.
If too stiff, add a few drops of milk to desired spreading consistency.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water over low heat until they are plump (20 to 30 minutes).
Drain raisin liquid into measuring cup.
Add enough water to make 1/2 cup.
Heat oven to 400°.
Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in raisin liquid.
Blend flour and other dry ingredients and stir in.
Add rolled oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet; bake about 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, corn syrup, salt, vanilla and margarine. Spread nuts in bottom of shell.
Pour in filling.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy dinner rolls
directions: Soften the yeast in warm water.
Scald milk; add sugar, salt and
shortening.
Cool.
Add
cups flour and mix well. Add egg; add
enough
flour
to
make soft dough. Turn out on floured board
and	knead
until smooth.
Put in greased bowl, until double in bulk.
Punch down; shape in rolls and place in greased muffin
tins.
Let rise double in bulk.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Slice all vegetables and toss with olive oil and soup mix. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring once.

title: holiday breakfast
directions: Trim crusts from bread and crumble.
Mix bread and cheese in bottom of greased 7 1/2x12 flat baking dish.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Stir in salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Lay bacon on top.
Refrigerate over night.
Next morning, bake uncovered at 350° for 50-55 minutes.
Will sink if allowed to sit too long.
Serves 6.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix in mixer real soft dough all ingredients but confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Can put close together.
After cooling a few minutes, roll in sugar.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: dieters delight strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thickened. Cool, then add strawberries. Pour into baked pie shell. Top with whip topping.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat eggs and add to butter and sugar.
Add mashed bananas, flour, nuts and vanilla.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes in glass pan at 350°.

title: grape juice
directions: Use 1/2 gallon jars. Fill jars with grapes and sugar, then the rest of jar with boiling water.
Can be processed in boiling water bath for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Remove jackets and mash real good, then add eggs, oleo or butter and sugar.
Mix well.
Add milk to make a soft mixture, then add allspice.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done, about 40 minutes.

title: broiled steak with spicy potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to broil.
Make the Spicy Seasoning Mix. Arrange the potatoes on one half of a broiler pan(s); place the frozen steak on the other half.

Combine the oil and 2 teaspoons of the Spicy Seasoning Mix; brush potatoes with half the mixture. Broil first side of steak and potatoes with the surface of the steak about 5 inches from the heat, for about 14 minutes; turn steak and potatoes.
Brush potatoes with remaining seasoned oil. Continue broiling steak for 13 to 18 minutes until steak is rare (140°) to medium (180°).
Continue broiling potatoes for 8 to 10 minutes more or until potatoes are done and tender.
Season steak and potatoes with salt, if desired. Yields 4 servings.

title: port cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce, wine, nuts and pineapple and let set up in refrigerator.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese and spread over top of jello.

title: 5 layer salad
directions: Add 1 layer
of broken lettuce, sliced water chestnuts, sliced onion and frozen
peas.
Spread
a thin layer of mayonnaise.
Add cheese on top (sprinkle as desired).
Add crumbled bacon pieces. Chill.

title: upside down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 13
x
9-inch pan with butter.
Put pecans and coconut in bottom
of
pan.
Pour
prepared cake mix over this layer.
Melt cream cheese and butter.
Add confectioners sugar to cream
cheese and butter.
Pour over cake (before cooking). Cook according to directions on box.
Serve in pan.

title: layered pea salad
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish, layer the lettuce, celery, pepper, eggs, onion, peas and bacon.
Mix salad dressing with sugar.
Spread on top of layers.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Refrigerate until ready.
Serve with 1 cup Italian dressing. Serves 8 to 10.

title: squash bake
directions: Saute onion in skillet sprayed with non-stick cooking spray. Combine squash, soup and sour cream in bowl. Add onion, carrot, salt and pepper; mix well. Fold in bread crumbs. Spoon into a 2-quart casserole. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: the greatest divinity
directions: In 3 quart bowl, mix sugar, syrup, and water for 12 minutes or so until spins a fine thread.
Add salt and egg whites and beat on high until stiff.
Pour syrup in thin stream into mixture while beating constantly until mixture loses shine and thickens.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Yields approximately 30 pieces.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and oleo together.
Cool.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Form in roll on waxed paper.
Roll in coconut; refrigerate.
Slice in slices to serve.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a 2 to 3 pound container.
When ready to use, mix 1/3 cup chocolate mixture to one cup of hot water.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into bite size balls.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Good to make and freeze for later.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs 1 at a time and beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift 2 cups flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add sifted mixture to cream mixture and beat.
Dredge berries in remaining flour and fold into main mixture.
Pour in buttered and coated with sugar tube pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cashew chip beef bake
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery in margarine over medium heat. Arrange beef mixture and noodles in layers in greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine soups, milk and seasonings.
Pour over beef and noodles.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour. Uncover and sprinkle with potato chips and nuts and bake 10 more minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: grandma's barbecue sauce
directions: Chop onions and peppers, then saute in stockpot.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer at least 1 hour.
Great with roast pork or roast beef.

title: aunt nancy's cake(texas sheet cake)
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Mix butter, water and cocoa, then boil.
Add to first mixture.
Bake 20 minutes on cookie sheet or 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Add undrained pineapple to pudding mix.
Let stand 15 minutes. Add next ingredients and chill overnight.

title: pineapple spread
directions: Mix flour and sugar together in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water until it thickens.
Add egg, salt, margarine, lemon juice and pineapple.
Will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix and chill ingredients except crescent rolls.
Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Press like one piece dough.
Bake about 8 to 10 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.
Spread chilled mix on top of dough.
Cut vegetables desired and sprinkle on top (about 5 kinds, carrots, celery, onion, peppers, broccoli and cauliflower).
Finish with one cup shredded Cheddar cheese. Makes 60 squares.

title: garlic bubble loaf
directions: Blend together oleo, egg, garlic powder, parsley flakes and salt (optional).
Cut off or tear off small pieces of dough, about the size of walnuts.
Dip into oleo mixture.
Place pieces of dough into greased loaf pan until all dough is used up.
Cover; let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool slightly.

title: pear salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix in the cream cheese until melted.
Add pear juice and cut up pears.
Let set until it begins to jell.
Fold Cool Whip into jello mixture.
Refrigerate.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Mix all above ingredients together.
Bake in a lightly greased and floured bunt pan for 40 minutes.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Heat soup and mix with rest of ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can add more cheese on top or butter crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cream cheese and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add sour cream and mix.
Add vanilla and mix.
Put in 9-inch round pan.
(Can mix graham crackers and butter and spread in pan for crust.)
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave door closed 1 hour, then
door open 1
hour.

title: "georgie porgie"
directions: Mix together the flour, pecans and butter.
(Reserve a few pecans for top.)
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes; cool.
Mix in mixer the 4x sugar and softened cream cheese.
Fold in the Cool Whip (reserve some Cool Whip).
Spread over cooled first layer.
Blend the puddings with the milk.
When set, spoon over the second layer and spread to cover.
Top with reserved Cool Whip and pecans.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat milk to scalding.
In a pan, mix cocoa, sugar and flour. Mix well.
Add milk slowly.
Cook until thick.
Take off stove. Add egg yolks.
Also, vanilla.
Stir well.
Put into baked pie shell.

title: breakfast sausage and egg souffle
directions: Brown crumbled sausage in a heavy skillet.
Drain well on paper towels.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
The next day, bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.
This dish is very good for a brunch or supper.
I usually serve it with fresh fruit, strawberries, cantaloupe, peaches or whatever is in season.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Cook ground beef and onion over medium heat until beef is brown and onion is soft, but do not brown onion. Drain fat off. Add seasoned salt, sour cream, and Worcestershire sauce, stirring to mix well. Press the beef mixture into a 2 qt. casserole dish. Spread mashed potatoes over the meat and top with cheese. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: almond mini chip shortbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add flour and almond extract; blend well.
Stir in small chocolate chips; pat into prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Makes about 36 bars.

title: peach conserve
directions: Mix peaches and Sure-Jell.
Bring to a full rolling boil and boil for 1 minute stirring constantly.
Then add sugar slowly and bring back to boil and boil 1 minute.
take off stove and add cherries, vanilla and rinds.
Stir and skim off foam.
Seal in sterilized jars.
Serve on top of ice cream.

title: creole cornbread dressing
directions: Brown meat with half the celery, onions, bell peppers and garlic (if desired). When brown, add chicken broth. Remove from fire and add all remaining ingredients; mix well. Bake at 375° until firm and golden brown.

title: silkyways frappe(milky ways)
directions: Melt
the
chocolate; pour 1/2 cup chocolate over 1 cup marshmallow cream.
Mix well and chill (filling).

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Fry meat lightly on low, crumbling as it cooks with celery and onion until they are transparent.
Add rest of ingredients, except noodles.
Mix thoroughly; place in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour at 350°; after 1/2 hour, reduce heat to 300° and cover with noodles.
Bake for another 30 to 45 minutes.

title: celery salad
directions: Chop celery into cubes.
Shred cabbage.
Mix oil, sugar, vinegar, grated onion, salt and pepper.
Pour dressing over celery and cabbage.

title: our favorite christmas eggnog
directions: Combine well the eggs, Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and salt until thoroughly blended.
Gradually beat in milk.
Gently fold in whipped cream.
Pour into punch bowl or serving cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: mom callanan's irish soda bread
directions: Combine all ingredients but buttermilk.
Mix well.
Slowly stir in buttermilk until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Knead on floured board until smooth. Shape into a ball.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Flatten into a 7-inch circle.
Make a cross with sharp knife 1/4-inch deep on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until light brown on top.
Pour melted butter on top after baking.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, chopped nuts and flour together in a large bowl.
Stir in melted butter and mix with two forks until lightly crumbly like pie crust.
Remove 1 cup of mixture to be used later as topping.
Place remainder in 8-inch square pan and press firmly.
Bake for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese until smooth with 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat in lemon juice, egg, milk and vanilla.
Pour this onto the baked crust.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Return to oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly, then cut in 2-inch squares.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: blueberry pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 8-inch square pan.
Stir in brown sugar and pineapple.
Arrange pecan halves onto pineapple mixture.
Combine muffin mix, milk and chopped pecans. Blend well.
Spread batter over pineapple mixture and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate immediately.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Then add carrots, oil and eggs.
Beat until well mixed.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Empty package of pudding into bowl. Drain juice from pineapple over pudding and mix well. Add pineapple and whipped topping; mix well. Can be served frozen or unfrozen. Yield: 6 servings.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients. Shape into 1 large or 2 small loaves.
Bake in deep skillet 1 1/2 hours.

title: fluffy mustard sauce
directions: Mix sugar, mustard and beaten egg yolks in top of small double boiler.
Add vinegar and consomme and heat thoroughly.
Add seasonings.
Fold into stiffly beaten egg whites and continue cooking about 5 minutes.
Serve with ham, beef or fish. Approximate yield:
6 portions.

title: chicken with walnuts
directions: Skin, halve lengthwise and bone chicken breasts.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces; set aside.
In small bowl stir soy sauce into cornstarch; stir in dry sherry, ginger root, sugar, salt and red pepper; set aside.
Preheat a wok or large skillet over high heat. Add cooking oil.
Stir-fry green peppers and green onions in hot oil for 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove from wok or skillet.
Add walnuts to wok or skillet.
Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes or until just golden.
Remove from wok or skillet.
(Add more oil if necessary.)
Add half of the chicken to the hot wok or skillet. Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove from wok or skillet.
Stir-fry remaining chicken 2 minutes.
Return all chicken to wok or skillet. Stir soy mixture; stir into chicken.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Lower heat.
Stir in vegetables and walnuts; cover and cook 1 minute more.
Serve chicken and vegetables at once.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients, except snow.
When well mixed, fold in enough snow to make mixture thick.
Eat at once.

title: lori's pea salad(pleasin' pea salad)
directions: Thaw peas right in fridge in the bag.
Add water chestnuts, olives, celery, green onions and cheese.
Bind together with mayonnaise that has a small amount of lemon juice and a dash of nutmeg.

title: tropical tiger
directions: Whirl 1 medium size cut up ripe banana and chilled pineapple juice in blender.
Serve in tall glass with ice.

title: crock-pot corn casserole
directions: With crock-pot on high, melt cream cheese, butter and 1/2 cup of milk.
Mix other 1/2 cup of milk with flour.
Pour flour and milk with cream cheese mixture in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Add corn, peppers and pimiento.
Cook on low for 4 hours.

title: butter baked carrots
directions: Place 1 inch of water in a saucepan; add carrots.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Meanwhile, in another saucepan, saute celery and onion in 3 tablespoons butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended.
Gradually whisk in milk.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Drain carrots; place in a greased 8 inch square baking dish.
Top with the white sauce.
Melt the remaining butter and toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over the top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until mixture is bubbly and topping is golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in oil in large skillet or pot.
Stir in tomatoes, corn, salt, chili powder and pepper. Let simmer for five minutes.
Stir in the corn meal mixed with water. Cover and let simmer ten minutes.
Add olives and turn into three-quart casserole.
(Leave room at top for Spoon Bread.)
The secret to this recipe is the Spoon Bread on top.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Stuff chicken breasts with ham and cheese.
Use toothpick to hold breast together.
Roll breast in milk.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and egg yolks.
Fold in Cool Whip into mixture.
Tear angel food cake into real small pieces.
Place half of pieces in a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Spread half creamy mixture over cake, also half of crushed candy bars and nuts.
Repeat again with layers of cake and creamy mixture, then crushed candy bars. Let chill.
Ummmmm-good and rich.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix together all the ingredients, making sure it is well creamed.
Makes 1 3/4 cups or enough for one 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Whip egg whites and set aside.
Dissolve 1 bar chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add beaten egg yolks; mix well.
Add 3/4 cup of milk alternately with flour.
Add soda to 1/4 cup milk; add to batter and mix well.
Add vanilla and chocolate.
Fold in egg whites. Bake at 350° in four 9-inch layer pans until done.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a blender, combine the first 4 ingredients; blend for 2 minutes or until well blended. Pour into a large mixing bowl and gently fold Cool Whip in. In a separate large bowl or dish, layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture. Keep layering until all is used up. Keep stored in refrigerator.

title: pecan crisps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, sugar and salt into bowl.
Mix in thoroughly with fork the shortening, egg yolk, milk and vanilla.
Form into balls the size of a small walnut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press 1/16-inch thick with bottom of greased glass dipped in sugar.
Brush with slightly beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with finely chopped pecans.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Pour off grease.
Add catsup, brown sugar, ground mustard, vinegar and salt.
Stir in all beans using all juices from beans.
Stir thoroughly.
Bake uncovered at 375° in a conventional oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: pound cake (chocolate optional)
directions: For Chocolate Pound Cake add 1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa and 2 tablespoons grated unsweetened chocolate (1 square).

title: biscuit mix
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut into shortening until it resembles a coarse corn meal.
Store loosely in airtight container.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and egg.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Top with M&M's.

title: cauliflower supreme
directions: Use any or all of the following vegetables:
Cut unpeeled acorn squash in rings, peeled or scrubbed parsnips and carrots in quarters lengthwise, scrubbed red skinned or sweet potatoes in 1 1/2 to 2-inch chunks and peeled onions in wedges.
Spread vegetables in a single layer in 1 or 2 baking pans or baking sheets with sides. Drizzle with vegetable or olive oil, then sprinkle with salt, pepper and dried thyme or dried rosemary to taste.
Bake in a 450° oven, turning every 10 minutes or so, for 30 minutes or until lightly browned and tender.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add margarine.
Blend with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse meal. Add yeast and buttermilk.
Mix and add more flour, if necessary to make soft dough.
Knead about 30 strokes.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick; cut out with a 2 to 3-inch cutter and bake at 450° until brown.
Dough will keep covered in refrigerator 4 to 6 days. Knead all the dough down each time some is used.

title: apple streusel dessert
directions: Lightly grease and flour a 9 X 13 pan. In a large bowl, combine first 3 ingredients; beat until moistened. Continue to beat on medium speed for 4 minutes. Pour into prepared pan. Mix last 4 ingredients together; sprinkle over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool slightly before cutting.

title: glazed fudge brownie almond pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
In a 2-quart casserole, mix all ingredients together, except for 1/2 cup bread cubes.
Sprinkle top with remaining bread cubes and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
For even better taste, top with grated cheese and put under broiler until bubbly brown.

title: easy oriental chicken
directions: Combine chicken, cornstarch, soy sauce, ginger, garlic and salt.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add mixture; cook for 3 minutes.
Add brown sugar, vinegar and 1/4 c.
water. Cover; simmer for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add pineapple to chicken mixture; continue cooking, uncovered, for 10 minutes more. Ready!
Serves 4.

title: banana-prune cake
directions: Stir shortening just to soften.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add bananas and half the milk; mix well until all flour is dampened, then beat vigorously 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining milk; beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in prunes and nuts.

title: meatballs and sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat water with egg. Stir in bread crumbs, horseradish and water chestnuts.
Add ground chuck.
Gently mix with hands into 1-inch balls.
Place in shallow pan and bake 12 minutes.
Serve with Hot Marmalade Soy Dip.
Makes 44.

title: rice casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion a little; add rest of ingredients. Dissolve the bouillon cubes in 3 cups hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Line pan with graham wafers (not crushed).
In a large bowl, mix the pineapple and instant pudding powder together.
Add lemon juice and 1/2 tub of Dream Whip.
Beat all ingredients together. When it becomes thick, spread over graham wafers, then use other 1/2 of Dream Whip for the top.
You may then decorate the top with chopped walnuts or graham wafer crumbs.
Yields 12 servings.

title: old virginia stew
directions: Brown meat in hot fat.
Add hot water, onion, lemon juice, seasonings and tomato juice and simmer for 2 hours.
Add water if needed.
Add vegetables and cook until done.

title: taco soup
directions: In a large pot, saute beef, onion and green chilies.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes on low.
Top with crushed tortilla chips and grated cheese.
Top with sour cream and/or black olives (optional).

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and save juice.
Add juice to the milk to make 3/4 cup of liquid.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Blend eggs, salmon and other ingredients.
Spoon into pan and shape.
Bake 45 minutes until top is golden and crisp. Serve hot or cold.

title: lemonade pie(no cooking)
directions: Mix with a spoon or hand mixer.
Pour in pie shell.
Freeze it for 1 hour and eat.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Heat milk and oil.
Mix with dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes. Add egg; beat.
Add more flour (until you can knead the dough). Knead several minutes.
Let rise in a greased large bowl until double in volume.
Punch down; let rest 10 minutes.
Pinch off and form into rolls.
Let rise until double again.
Oil tops of rolls. Bake in preheated 425° oven until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish. Mix all ingredients together; place in buttered dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raspberry cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom and sides of 9-inch tube pan or 9 x 10-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl, combine flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
Using pastry blender or fork, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture.
To remaining crumb mixture add baking powder, baking soda, salt, sour cream, extract and 1 egg.
Blend well.
Spread dough over bottom of pan and one inch up the sides.
In a small bowl combine cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 egg.
Blend well.
Pour into dough-lined pan.
Carefully spoon preserves evenly over cheese mixture.
In a small combine reserved crumb mixture and almonds. Sprinkle over preserves.
Bake at 350° until cream cheese is set and crust is deep golden brown (for 45 to 55 minutes).
Remove from pan.
Serve warm or cool, cut in wedges.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put broccoli in bowl.
Add the onion, bacon and cheese.
Mix ingredients well.
Add mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Blend it all thoroughly.
Let cool in refrigerator for a few minutes. Serves 6 people.

title: mock curry chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Add to boiling chicken the carrots, celery, onion, garlic and bouillon cube.
Okay to use whole chicken if you prefer to.
Mix remaining ingredients all together. Save stock from chicken to use later in other dishes, such as chicken dressing/stuffing.
Can freeze chicken stock.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Add the oil, vanilla, sugar and squash to the beaten eggs.
Mix well the sifted flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; add flour mixture to squash mixture.
Stir in 1 cup of chopped nuts. Bake in 5 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch loaf pan for 1 hour or until done at 325°.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook roast in the morning and let cool.
In a large pan, combine the sugar, soup, celery and onion.
Pick roast apart and add to mixture.
Cook 45 minutes on low heat, stirring often. Serve on buns.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer until creamy.
Add 1 cup powdered sugar and stir in the Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells.
Freeze.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Mix and spread over bars while still hot.

title: coconut punch cake
directions: Prepare cake per package instructions and bake in a 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Mix sugar, milk, coconut and flavoring.
Bring to a boil.

title: spinach dip
directions: Hollow out the loaf of
rye bread, saving the bread for dipping.
Combine all
other
ingredients.
Serve
in the hollowed out loaf of bread.

title: giant gingerbread people cookies
directions: Cookies:
Beat butter and sugars.
Add molasses and eggs.
Add combined flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Mix at low speed.
Divide dough into 3 portions.
Wrap each; chill on 17 x 14-inch cookie sheet.
Roll out each portion to 1/8-inch thickness. Use patterns to cut 2 people from one portion.
Remove excess dough (reserve).
Repeat with two remaining portions and reserved dough. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove to wire rack; cool.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter and brown sugar in a 9-inch cake pan.
Arrange pineapple slices and cherries in sugar mixture.
Any fruit may be used.
In bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat remaining 8 tablespoons butter and white sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Beat in half the flour, then milk and finally remaining flour.
Spread over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean.
Cool 3 minutes; turn onto a platter.
Leave 1 minute before removing pan.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place popped popcorn in brown paper bags.
Mix 1 cup brown sugar, butter and Karo syrup in large bowl.
Microwave for 4 minutes.
Then add vanilla and baking soda; stir until changes color.
Pour over popcorn in bag.
Shake well.
Place in microwave 1 minute and 40 seconds.
Shake well.
Microwave 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Shake again.
Microwave 1 minute.
Spread on cookie sheet to cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes; drain well. Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese together; mix well. Add broccoli to the mixture and stir well. Pour into a baking dish. Sprinkle the stuffing mix evenly over the top (just to cover thinly) and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes or until good and bubbly.

title: beehive cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add to batter. Bake at 375° 25 minutes in 8-inch square pan.

title: pink arctic salad
directions: Soften cheese.
Blend Miracle Whip and sugar together.
Add fruit; fold in whipped cream.
(Fruit includes cranberry sauce and pineapple.)
Freeze.
Serves 10.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly. Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and marshmallow.
Place in 8 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: barbara's chicken and artichokes
directions: Place artichokes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chicken.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Pour over top; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken chop suey
directions: Mix all together in a saucepan and cook for 45 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each. Fold in 2/3 of cream.
Turn into pie shell and chill at least 2 hours.
Decorate with remaining cream.
Freezes well.

title: crisp onion-roasted potatoes
directions: In shallow baking pan, blend all ingredients except potatoes. Mix well.
Add potatoes and turn to coat thoroughly.
Bake, stirring occasionally.
Bake in oven at 450° for 60 minutes. Garnish with chopped parsley.
Serves 8.

title: churros
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add butter and salt.
Add flour and remove from heat.
Beat with a fork until well mixed.
Beat in the eggs and cinnamon.
Put the mixture into a pastry bag.
Heat about an inch of oil in a pan or use a deep fryer to about 350°. Squeeze the mixture into the oil, making the churros about 7 inches long.
Cook 3 to 5 at a time, depending on how large your skillet or pan is until they are a nice golden color, turning occasionally.
Drain on paper towels.
Transfer to another dish; sprinkle sifted powdered sugar over them and serve immediately. Makes about 18.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut meat into strips.
If using shrimp, shell and devein. Marinate in soy sauce.
Prepare vegetables by slicing diagonally or into flowerets.
Slice onions and crush garlic and heat in 2 to 3 tablespoons oil in medium to large skillet.
Reduce heat when oil starts to smoke.
Saute onions and garlic until transparent but not burnt.
Add meat pieces.
Saute for at least 5 minutes. Add 2 cans of broth or 2 cups of tap water.
(I use a bouillon cube.) Simmer until meat is tender.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Add vegetables.
It's up to you if you want your veggies half or fully cooked.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour in sugar; melt margarine.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts last.
Pour in unbaked pie shells and bake at 375° about 40 minutes until brown.
May be served with unsweetened whipped cream.

title: princess brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on package.
Combine softened cream cheese and sugar; mix until well blended.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Spread brownie batter onto bottom of greased 15 x 9-inch baking pan, reserve 1/2 cup batter.
Cover with cream cheese mixture; spoon on reserved batter.
Cut through batter with knife several times for a marbled effect.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: hawaiian harvest coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine sugar, brown sugar, cream cheese, and butter. Mix well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add extract and mix. Add flour to batter alternately with the milk. Pour into a greased and floured 9x13x2 inch baking pan.

In small bowl, combine preserves, cinnamon, and ginger. Mix well. Drop the pineapple mixture from a teaspoon onto batter. Sprinkle pecans over top of batter. Using a knife cut through the batter several times for marbled effect. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of coffeecake. Drizzle glaze over top.

title: cherry bonanza
directions: Melt butter and pour in graham cracker crumbs.
Pat in bottom of a square cake pan.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar; add Dream Whip to mixture.
Pour in pan; spread pie filling on top.

title: it's not a candy cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lay greased tin foil on a cookie sheet, allowing foil to hang over edge.
Cover foil with saltine crackers side by side (approximately 40).

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into pan.
Chop fruit and nuts into small pieces.
Mix together in large bowl.
Mix sugar and flour. Stir into juice.
Place on burner to heat.
Beat egg into hot mixture, making a sauce.
Let sauce cool.
Drain juice from fruit mixture.
Pour sauce over fruit.
Top with marshmallows.

title: skillet corn fritters
directions: In medium pan, melt butter.
Add corn, green pepper and onion. Cook 8 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Add eggs, milk and hot sauce.
Mix well.
Stir in cool vegetable mixture.

title: callie's crumb cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter or margarine.
Add raisins, egg, sour milk or cream and soda.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: brown butter icing
directions: Melt butter or margarine over a low heat until golden brown. Remove from fire and add sugar, cream, water and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cutlet parmesan(pork, chicken or veal)
directions: Mix egg,
bread
crumbs and meat; fry with medium flame until golden
brown.
Place
1 layer meat in baking dish.
Top with sauce
and sprinkle with cheese.
Continue layering dish until 1-inch
from
top of dish.
Place in middle rack in 325° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve with fresh salad and garlic bread.

title: toast
directions: Place bread in toaster; set at medium.
Push knob down.
Wait 5 minutes.
Plug toaster in.
Wait 1 minute.
Remove bread. Spread butter on bread.
Cut in half.
Serve quickly.

title: angel biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, put yeast, sugar and water.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Heat buttermilk to lukewarm.
Add flour mixture to yeast mixture, then add oil and buttermilk.
Stir together until dough forms.
Turn dough out on floured board.
Knead 10 times.
Gather into a ball and put in greased bowl, turning over to grease top. Cover with cloth.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down dough.
Place on floured board.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased pan.
Let rise 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add butter and chocolate which have been melted in a double boiler.
Add flour, nuts and baking powder. Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat the olive oil in a saucepan over low heat.
Add the butter and simmer until melted.
Add onions and saute until golden.
Add ground beef and bacon, sauteing until brown, stirring occasionally. Add garlic, parsley, salt, black and red pepper.
Cook over low heat for at least 10 minutes.
Pour in the wine; cover and steam for a few minutes more.
Now you are ready to add the tomatoes, puree and paste.
Bring this mixture to the boiling point and add the carrot and celery.
Cover again and cook over very low heat for one hour, stirring occasionally.
This is enough sauce for 4 people.
If you need to make a larger amount, just double the recipe.
You can always make extra and freeze it.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: Pour oil in bottom of a 6-quart saucepot.
Place meat and all spices to brown.
Add tomato paste and 3 tomato paste cans of water.
Let simmer.
Put cans of tomatoes through blender.
Add into pot.
Cover.
Allow to cook down about 3 hours on low heat, stirring frequently.
(This is the best!!)

title: stuffed artichokes(sicily)
directions: Wash artichokes and spread leaves apart.
Cut the top of each leaf off to make straight edges.
Mix bread crumbs with olive oil until moistened.
Add garlic.
Stuff in between each leaf on artichoke.

Place in deep pan, standing upright, so they are snug. Add about 1 cup water or enough to cover 1/3 bottom of artichokes. Heat to boil, cover and simmer about 40 to 45 minutes or until leaves pull out easily.

title: yum yum cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla; set aside.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Then add to the creamed mixture.
Blend into mixture nutmeats, coconut and oatmeal and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Make balls by the tablespoon.
Roll in powdered sugar and flatten with greased glass bottom and bake 10 minutes in a 325° to 350° oven.

title: doritos pie casserole
directions: Brown together the ground beef and onion.
Grease a 3-quart Pyrex dish and place a single layer of Doritos in the bottom. Combine the beef mixture with the refried beans and spoon this over the Doritos.
Next, spoon the tomato sauce on top.
Sprinkle with the grated cheese and top with another layer of Doritos. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes and top with taco sauce, if desired.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Cool.
Combine brown sugar and pineapple in saucepan.
Cook until thickens.
Allow to cool. Prepare pudding as directed.
Pour brown sugar mixture over cake. Next, pour pudding on top.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding. Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix softened oleo and graham crackers.
Layer on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Mix in mini marshmallows.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
On top, pour cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: taco mix pie bake surprise!
directions: Cook meat and onion together.
Drain grease.
Add can of refried beans.
Line a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan with the crescent rolls.
Pinch together like a crust.
Spread meat mixture on top. Mix together sour cream, egg and cheese.
Pour on top of meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with chopped lettuce, tomato, chopped onions and taco sauce.

title: tasty jello mold(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Dissolve jello with boiled pineapple juice.
Add enough water to equal 1 cup.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Let stand to cool.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Then add cool jello gradually.
Let stand until firm.
Add crushed pineapple and beat mixture well. Put in refrigerator until hard.
Easy, attractive and good!

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into baking dish and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix in pepper and onion.
Add melted, cut up cheese.
Add broth and soups.
Pour over spaghetti and mix well. Add chicken and mix.
Spread into a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350 for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: crock pot roast
directions: Pour enough oil in the bottom of a skillet to brown your roast on medium to high heat.
Sprinkle entire roast with Lawry's and brown well in skillet.
Set aside.
Mix tomatoes, soup, Worcestershire sauce and onion in crock pot.
Place roast in the crock pot and cook all day on low.
What a great gravy to serve with your roast and mashed potatoes!

title: corned beef
directions: Place all ingredients in a stone jar.
Cut meat, then place in jar.
When full, weight down with a rock.
Lift rock every few days so that brine will work around all of the meat.
After 14 days, the meat is ready to use.
Soak overnight in clear water before using.

title: whipped cheese pie(from 1975 edition)
directions: Combine cottage cheese, sugar, egg yolks, milk, vanilla and cornstarch.
Stir until smooth.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Fold into batter; put cinnamon on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: heath bars
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and butter until crumbly; put 1 cup aside.
To remaining mixture, add egg, milk, soda and vanilla and beat.
Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Break up Heath bars.
Sprinkle Heath bars, nuts and saved crumbs on top.

title: lemon lush
directions: Crust:	Cut 2 sticks butter into 2 cups flour until well blended.
Add nuts.
Pat
into
9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 400° for 17 minutes.
Let cool.

title: rellenos para tacos(chicken)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tortillas and saute in butter. Set aside.
Drop tortillas in hot oil, one at a time.
After a few seconds, turn, fold in half and fry to desired crispness.
Drain on paper towels and keep warm in a low-heat oven.
To serve, open each tortilla gently and insert filling.

title: cheese cake surprise
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy
smooth, adding eggs one at
a time.
Blend in sugar and
almond
extract.
Pour
into prepared pie plate.
Bake in preheated oven
at 350° for about 50 minutes. Let cool for about 20
minutes.
Stir sour cream, sugar and vanilla together and spread evenly over pie.
Return to oven and bake another 15 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: carrot mold
directions: Mix oil, sugar, salt, vanilla, water, lemon juice, flour and carrots together.
Separate 2 eggs.
Mix yolks with ingredients; refrigerate for 1 hour.
Beat egg whites with baking powder and baking soda; add to refrigerated mixture.
Grease pan; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pie - french-style
directions: Choose 10 to 15 large ripe berries and leave whole.
Mash the rest and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir in the sugar and cornstarch, which have been mixed together.
Cook slowly approximately 10 minutes, then let cool.
Line pie shell with softened cream cheese and raw whole berries.
Pour cooled mixture over top and cover with whipped cream.

title: grossenhausen strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift 1/2 cup flour with the baking powder.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Set aside. Beat egg yolks until thick and light.
Add sugar, gradually, and continue beating.
Add flavoring, water and 1 cup of the flour, alternating.
Then add the baking powder mixture.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into an ungreased tube pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Invert pan and when cool, remove cake. Mash enough strawberries to make 1 cup of juice.
Strain.
Thicken this with 1 tablespoon of cornstarch and boil 5 minutes.
Cover the top of the cake with perfect whole strawberries, stem side down, then pour the hot thickened strawberry juice over the top. Let stand until firm.
Chill and serve.

title: spareribs
directions: Place ribs in large, flat baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: rotini stir-fry
directions: Prepare rotini per package directions and drain.
In a large skillet, heat oil and add chicken, broccoli, carrots and onion. Cook and stir over medium heat until the broccoli is tender (crisp).
Add water, bouillon and tarragon, cook and stir until the chicken is cooked through.
Add hot cooked rotini and Parmesan cheese.
Toss to coat.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings. Contains per serving: 225 calories; 6 grams fat; 123 mg. sodium and 37 mg. cholesterol.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Bake covered in 325° oven for 2 hours.
Brown meat and seasoning in oil.
Add flour, salt, garlic powder, marjoram and pepper.
Stir in tomatoes and broth and mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Stir twice during baking.
Remove bay leaf.

title: gerbeau
directions: Place butter, egg yolks, sugar, vanilla, and bourbon in a large mixing bowl along with 4 cups of flour.
Knead thoroughly, gradually adding flour until the dough is pliable and doesn't stick to your hands.
You may need to add more than the indicated flour.
The pastry dough should be similar to pie crust dough. Chill the dough for 1/2 hour.
Place ground walnuts and confectioners sugar in a bowl and stir together.

title: mom's split pea soup
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Drain them.
The next day, saute onion and carrots in bacon fat until tender.
Add ham bone, garlic salt, pepper, marjoram and water to the drained peas.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover.
Simmer for 3 hours, stirring often.
Remove ham bone; trim off meat and return meat to soup.
Adjust seasoning.
Serve with hot croutons.

title: chicken with apples
directions: Season chicken; brown well on both sides in butter, then remove chicken.
Add onion and apples.
Cook until onion is soft. Blend in flour and stir until smooth.
Add stock and stir, over low heat, until smooth and thickened.
Add nutmeg.
Mix in brandy. Return chicken.
Cover and cook on low heat for 40 minutes. Remove chicken with apples and onion.
Add heavy cream and cook until just heated through.
Pour over the chicken.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients (except Hershey bars) together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a greased and floured 18 x 12-inch pan. Frost with your favorite frosting or lay Hershey bars over top of brownies as soon as you remove them from the oven.
As soon as they are glossy and soft, spread with a spatula until brownies are completely covered.
These need to cool several hours before cutting.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Fry mixture in butter. Cook 4 rounds (pancakes) at a time, about 2 to 3 minutes each side.

title: mini-mincemeat nut cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and beat well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with condensed milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in mincemeat and nuts.
Spoon batter into paper lined miniature (1 3/4-inch) muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Quarter one head of cabbage and parboil to almost tender. Drain and core.
Layer cabbage leaves in 9x13 greased pan with solid layers of sharp cheddar cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover with cracker crumbs and butter chunks.
Cover well with aluminum foil, and place in refrigerator until next day or continue the recipe.
Make a thin sauce (about 1 cup) of flour, sugar and milk.
Drizzle it over the cracker crumbs.
Cover again with foil, and punch holes to let the steam escape.
Place in preheated 375° oven for 60 to 90 minutes, or until nicely browned.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight or several hours before serving.

title: italian sausage spinach pie
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage and onion until sausage is done and onion is tender.
Drain well.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs; stir in remaining ingredients.
Fill pie shells.
Bake in 375° oven for 50 minutes.

title: black raspberry salad
directions: *May use orange Jell-O and mandarin oranges or lemon Jell-O and pineapple, etc.

title: icebox rolls *
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in lukewarm water.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and shortening to milk; stir until shortening melts. Cool.
Add yeast mixture and enough flour to make a thick batter; add egg and beat.
Let rise until double.
Add remaining flour. Cover and refrigerate overnight or until cold.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness; cut, dip in melted butter and fold over.
Place on greased pan and let rise 1 1/2 hours (cover while rising). Remaining dough may be stored in a greased, covered bowl in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces; place into casserole dish. Add Veg-All, soup and broth.
Mix milk, Bisquick and margarine together; pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aunt ruby's easy corn pudding
directions: Beat egg, milk, sugar and cornstarch.
Add creamed corn.
Mix and put into lightly greased baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: burger with cottage cheese
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in melted butter for 4 minutes. Cut Redi-burger in half inch cubes and add with crumbs to onion mixture.
Stir gently.
Spread evenly over bottom of a shallow baking dish.
Beat cottage cheese until almost smooth; add basil. Blend in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Pour cottage cheese mixture over Redi-burger layer and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken n dumplings 2
directions: Boil chicken, debone and cut into small pieces.
Use all the seasoning when boiling chicken.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in brown paper bag.
In a microwave dish, cook brown sugar, syrup and butter until it boils.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Remove from microwave and add baking soda.
Stir well.
It will foam up.
Pour over popcorn in paper bag.
Shake well.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove and shake well.
Cook another 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake well.
Spread out on cookie sheet to cool.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Adding cornbread mix last, add all ingredients together.
Put in greased muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Bake in tube pan.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together all the ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes.

title: "walldorf" chicken
directions: Put chopped onion on each chicken breast and roll it, securing with bacon wrapped around each breast.
Salt and pepper.
Brown rolled chicken breasts in butter in frying pan.
Put in rectangle casserole dish as close as possible.
