Mix cream of mushroom soup and sherry and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover the last 10 minutes to brown well.

title: baked potato dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put into a hollowed out loaf of round bread.
Bread 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with bread from round loaf, crackers or chips.

title: french bread pizza
directions: Cut bread in half and toast for 15 minutes at 300°.
Remove from oven and spread sauce over bread. Sprinkle with oregano to taste. Add toppings of choice and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve hot with crackers.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Melt Jello in hot water; let cool and thicken.
Fold in other ingredients.
Chill.

title: chocolate cherry angel food cake(cholesterol-free dessert)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine nuts, cherries, chocolate chips and cake flour mixture (red "B" packet) in large bowl.
Prepare, bake and cool cake following package directions.
Heat frosting until thin.
Glaze cake allowing frosting to drizzle down sides. Garnish with cherries or nuts, if desired.
White vanilla or cherry frosting may be used.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
Combine with chopped vegetables. Combine dressing ingredients and gently stir into mixture. Marinate overnight, stirring occasionally.
Double ingredients to serve large group.

title: ham quiche filling
directions: Cut ham into small pieces.
Place ham and grated Swiss cheese into the uncooked pastry shell.
Combine eggs, flour, milk, cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over the ham and cheese. Add melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut English muffins in half and arrange on cookie sheet.
Spread Ragu pizza sauce over each muffin. Sprinkle cheese over tops of muffins.
Add toppings, if desired.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix.
Bring this to a boil; then add cucumber mixture.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Put in a jar and seal.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients in mixer for 20 minutes.
Use Bundt or ring pan.
Put in cold oven.
Turn oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly beef crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk. Shape by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet, brown and cook meatballs.
Remove and keep warm. Pour off fat from skillet.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth.
Pour into skillet, cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute; add meat, pineapple and green pepper.
Heat through.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Add salt.
Pour 2 quarts of boiling water over ground mixture.
Let stand about 5 minutes; drain well. Add sugar and vinegar to ground mixture.
Cook 20 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: robin's broccoli soup
directions: Add broccoli, onion, butter, broth to pan. Cook until broccoli is tender.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook on low until cheese is melted.
Mix water and cornstarch, then add to soup. Stir until thickened.
Serve warm.

title: apple stew
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Stir in apple juice and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir in onions and carrots.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add apples during the last 5 minutes.
Blend flour and water together; stir into pan juices. Cook and stir until thickened.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Cut ribs in pieces desired; season with salt and pepper.
Brown on all sides.
Sprinkle smoked salt.
Add 1 cup water, cover and steam in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine beaten eggs with mashed bananas until light.
Sift together the flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add this to banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Put in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift together corn meal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add egg, milk and shortening; mix well by hand until all ingredients are well blended.
Bake in 8-inch square pan or greased muffin pans 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn bread(healthy)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix ingredients while heating the corn bread pan with the corn oil in it on the stove.
As soon as the pan and its oil are bubbly hot, pour corn bread mixture into the pan and place in oven.
When the corn bread is brown on the bottom (approximately 10 minutes), turn the oven to broil to brown the top of it.
Enjoy.
Day-old corn bread can be reheated by sprinkling a tiny bit of water on it and then reheating.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 9 x 1 1/4-inch or 12 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Blend all ingredients together.
Pour in pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clear.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: sawmill gravy
directions: To make Sawmill Gravy, use bacon drippings or fried ham grease left in the skillet after frying the meat and taking it out.
Add flour to the hot grease and let it brown slightly.
Thin the mixture a little with water, then add milk and salt and pepper. Stir and cook until fairly thick.

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a casserole dish. Bake uncovered for 40 minutes at 375° to 400°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash and soup.
Put into casserole. Top with mixture of butter, cracker crumbs and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boston butt
directions: Preheat oven to 400.
Lightly grease casserole dish.
Place Boston butt in bag and soak in the Worcestershire sauce for 30 minutes to two hours.
Remove from bag and discard Worcestershire sauce.
Coat with brown sugar pressing into meat.
Place in baking dish.
Add apple juice to pan (do not pour apple juice over meat). Cover tightly and place in oven.
Turn temperature down to 200 and bake about 5 to 6 hours or until very tender.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare crust.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugars.
Beat until well blended. Blend in margarine.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake until set, about 1 hour.
Serve with a big dip of vanilla ice cream on each serving.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mash avocados with salt, pepper and dash of lemon juice.
Set aside.
Combine sour cream with mayonnaise and 2/3 package taco seasoning mix.
Set aside.
Combine grated cheeses and set aside.
In a medium size casserole dish, layer the ingredients in the following order:
bean dip, mashed avocados, green onions, sour cream mixture, cheeses, tomatoes, then olives.
Serve with Fritos.

title: hamburger pie
directions: In skillet, fry meat until lightly browned and onion is tender. Drain off grease; add salt and pepper, drained beans and soup. Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Mash potatoes while hot; add milk and egg.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon mounds of potatoes over casserole.
Sprinkle potatoes with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly. Mix in orange juice and rind.
Blend in the mixed dry ingredients. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: italian zucchini cheese pie
directions: Saute bacon until just crisp.
Crumble bacon after it's cooled down.
Using a heavy skillet (at least a 10-inch), saute onions, zucchini, mushrooms and eggplant in olive oil until tender.
Then stir in pimento, parsley and seasonings.

title: cooked graham crackers
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil; spray generously with Pam.

Lay out graham cracker squares and top with chopped or broken pecans. Cook butter, margarine and sugar in saucepan; bring to boil. Cook 3 minutes. After cooking 3 minutes, pour over graham crackers; bake in oven at 350° for exactly 9 minutes. Let cool and break apart.

title: chocolate sheath cake with icing
directions: In large bowl, sift together sugar and flour.
Set aside.
Put in saucepan margarine, cocoa, shortening and water.
Bring to boil. Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Stir well.
Add the buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix well and pour into greased 16 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Start the icing about 5 minutes before cake is done.
Put in saucepan, 1 stick margarine, 4 tablespoons cocoa and 6 tablespoons milk.
Bring to boil, then add powdered sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and chopped pecans (optional).
Beat and spread on cake while cake is hot.

title: potato puffs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Shape into balls. Roll in bread crumbs. Deep-fry 3 minutes or until golden. Drain on paper towels; serve hot.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook frozen broccoli; drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over broccoli in casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and pepper together.
Blend egg and milk together.
Add sugar.
Add to flour mixture gradually.
Stir in corn.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep hot fat. Fry until brown.
Drain and serve with maple syrup.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Crumble angel food
cake,
mix	strawberries.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, powdered
sugar
and
milk
together.
Fold together. Layer in a	large bowl, beginning with cake mixture then strawberries; ending with strawberries on top.
Refrigerate. Yum-Yum.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar well; add eggs.
Add mixed dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating after each addition. Stir in vanilla.
Pour in well greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Loosen sides from pan and invert on plate.
Spread with creamy frosting or top with Cool Whip and strawberries.

title: miss georgia's cookies
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom.
Add dry ingredients over nuts.
Sprinkle fruit on top.
Bake.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Put wafers in bottom of baking cups in muffin tin.
Beat the remaining ingredients together until light and fluffy.
Fill cups 3/4 full with cream mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Top with 1 tablespoon cherry pie filling and chill.
Makes 19 servings.
This is simple, but very good!

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Crush 1 cup berries and cook with water about 1 minute. Sieve.
Set aside, saving the juice.

title: angel food cake with crushed pineapple
directions: Put in bowl crushed pineapple and pudding.
Beat 1 minute. Let stand 20 minutes.
Whip Dream whip as directed or use Cool Whip.
Then add to pineapple mixture. Mix well.

title: corn waffles
directions: Mix flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, whisk egg, melted butter, water, corn and vanilla. Stir into flour mixture.
Cook waffles.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion together.
Drain off excess. Add the rest of the ingredients (juices and all) to the drained ground beef and onion.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with crackers, chips and cheese.
Can be placed in a crock-pot to heat.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large plastic bowl; toss. Cover and chill for at least 8 hours before serving.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Add water to pineapple juice to equal 1/2 cup.

title: easy caramels
directions: Melt butter in heavy sauce pan.
Add brown sugar and salt. Combine thoroughly. Blend in corn syrup.
Gradually add condensed milk, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over medium heat until candy reaches firm ball stage, about one half hour.
Remove
from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into well buttered 8 x 12 in. glass pan.
Cool thoroughly and cut into squares.

title: pinwheels
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread evenly on flour tortilla. (Not too thick or it will come out when you cut them.) Roll tortilla up and wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Slice into medium slices and serve.
Makes about 12 small tortillas or 7 large.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Mix brown sugar and whipping cream.
Microwave for 13 minutes. Add rest of ingredients and mix until almost cool.
Spoon quickly on waxed paper sprayed lightly with Pam.

title: spam jambalaya
directions: In a large skillet, saute Spam, onions, green pepper, celery and garlic until tender.
May use 1 tablespoon oil.
Add tomatoes, broth, thyme, hot pepper sauce and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil, stir in rice; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Discard bay leaf; sprinkle with parsley.

title: quackers(oyster cracker snack)
directions: Mix Hidden Valley Ranch original style dry dressing, dill weed, oil and garlic powder.
Pour over crackers and mix well. Better after it sets for a while.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Cook meat in oil, turning frequently, until brown, about 5 minutes.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add other ingredients.
Mix dough until it forms a smooth ball. Let dough rise until double in size (about 1 hour).
Place dough into an oiled 2-quart round casserole.
Allow to rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Brush with butter and serve warm.

title: hot dog appetizer
directions: Mix together. Put in casserole. Bake in a 325° oven for 3 hours.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: First layer undiluted soups, then add rice, mixing around soups.
Then add pieces of chicken; salt and pepper chicken.
Lay on top of rice and soup; dot pieces of chicken with butter or oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Fix potatoes as directed on box.
Add the rest of ingredients. Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: quick italian salad
directions: Toss first 5 ingredients in large salad bowl.
Pour dressing over all and toss lightly to coat.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Scald milk; add mixture of sugar, flour and cocoa.
Cook until begins to thicken and add beaten egg yolks.
Cook about 3 to 5 minutes.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Make meringue of 3 egg whites for top and brown.

title: kool congealed salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Add Jell-O and mix well.
Add all ingredients and mix very well.
Put in covered dish and let set in refrigerator for 1 hour or serve at once.

title: white delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: horrible sounding scrumptious chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot.
Cook 1 hour on high; 3 hours on low.
Add 1 heaping tablespoonful of flour to thicken sauce and serve over rice.
Better if made ahead and reheated.
Serves 4.

title: sugar and spice nuts
directions: Grease 2 cookie sheets with butter.
In heavy saucepan, combine the sugar and water.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking, without stirring, until syrup reaches the firm ball stage (244°).

title: breakfast crumb cake
directions: Mix together butter, shortening, sugar, flour and baking powder like pie dough.
Take out as much as needed for crumbs on top.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Put in greased pie pans.
If using crumbs, sprinkle on top.
Bake approximately 35 minutes at 350°.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix everything together in the blender until frothy.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using 3/4 bag chips in salad and 1/4 bag as topping.
Cook in a 350° oven until simmering.
Serve warm.

title: sparkling strawberry punch
directions: In covered blender at high speed, blend strawberries and undiluted lemonade concentrate until blended.
Pour strawberry mixture into a chilled punch bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except orange slices.
Stir punch until sugar is dissolved.

title: old-fashioned chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all remaining ingredients and additional water (if desired).
Cook until vegetables are tender or in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Do not pare cucumbers; slice thin and add onions.
Add salt. Cover with cracked ice and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 2 hours. Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumber mixture; heat just to a boil.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.

title: divinity
directions: Cook ingredients until it spins a thread.
Pour 1/2 onto whites of two eggs beaten stiffly.
Cook other half until it makes a hard ball in water.
Pour into egg mixture very slowly.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until creamy (by hand) for a very long time.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Follow directions on box for pudding; when thick, pour over cake mix.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour smokies
directions: Warm jelly with water or pineapple juice over medium heat until liquid.
Add pineapple chunks and Carolina Pride cocktail smokies.
Heat until warmed through.
Serve immediately.

title: red, white and blue salad
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve 1 package of jello in 9 x 13-inch pan or dish, using 2 cups boiling water.
Chill until firm.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Bring to boil the soup, water and gelatin.
Remove from heat and using wire whip, add cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise, shrimp, celery, green onions, water and crab meat (optional).
Mix.
Pour in mold and chill.	Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: roadie's cream potatoes
directions: Chop and boil potatoes until done.
Cream potatoes.
Mix sour cream, cheese and bacon bits.
Stir.
Top with cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: basic liver paste
directions: Place chicken livers (and livers of any fowl) and pork in 4 tablespoons butter and saute until just done.
Cool, add tarragon, salt, pepper and wine.
Place in food processor and pulse to render into thick paste by mixing in remaining 4 tablespoons butter.
Spread fried or baked toast with liver paste and place cooked fowl on each slice.
Pour sauce over meat and serve.
For 6 slices of toast.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Combine celery, pepper, onion, oil and garlic.
Heat until vegetables are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat, covered, on high until shrimp are cooked.

title: alpine casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add soup, chili powder and chiles.
Add milk.
Simmer for approximately 10 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Do not beat.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spoon onto a greased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Spray Pam in lasagne pan; brown meat and onion.
Spread thin layer of meat, layer tortillas, meat, 1/2 cheese and soup mixture. Top with tortillas; bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove and add remaining cheese; bake 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake until golden and bubbly at 350°.

title: phyllis' hot mustard dressing
directions: Beat together.
Add to mustard mixture and heat until thick. When cool, add mayonnaise, enough to make 2 cups.

title: summer vege salad
directions: Mix ingredients with Miracle Whip salad dressing as desired.

title: easy make lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Cook noodles as directed on box. Layer noodles, meat mixture, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Sprinkle ham or bacon, broccoli and mushrooms in deep dish unbaked crust.
Put a layer of grated or sliced Swiss cheese.
Mix all remaining ingredients together.
Beat good with fork.
Pour over vegetables and cheese in shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until top is brown and quiche is firm.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and 1/2 jar of caramel topping.
Mix walnuts and 1/2 jar caramel topping.
Pour second mixture over first mixture.
Slice apples and dip into mixture.
It's delicious!

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt. Add juice and stir until smooth. Add 1 1/2 cups of cheese and pineapple and mix. Put in 9 x 12-inch pan and top with melted butter and crackers. Sprinkle with cheese (1/2 cup). Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ants on a log
directions: Fill celery stalks with peanut butter after cleaning.
Arrange raisins in peanut butter in a row to resemble ants crawling on a log.

title: easy shrimp appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese together and chill.
When ready to serve, pour mixture over cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemon-pineapple cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix and salad oil.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Add Sprite and mix well (about 2 minutes.)
Pour into greased and floured 13x9x2 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
Cool and top with:

title: raindrops
directions: Combine sugar, milk and pudding mix in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir until mixture boils; cook at rolling boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Beat at high speed in small bowl of electric mixer for 3 to 4 minutes or until mixture holds shape.
Drop from teaspoon onto buttered cookie sheet.
Store in cool place.
Children can help with recipe.

title: beer dip
directions: Blend and add 1 can flat beer (open the day before).
Whip up. Will keep indefinitely.

title: john's monkey meat
directions: Grind bologna and pickles together.
Add sweet relish and mayo.
Mix well and chill.
Spread on bread for sandwiches.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Cook to soft ball stage all ingredients except vanilla and pecans, then add vanilla and beat until thickened.
Add pecans, stirring until well coated and turn onto greased platter or waxed paper.
(I use wax paper.)
Separate into individual pieces.

title: apricot walnut balls
directions: In a bowl, combine apricots and coconut.
Add milk;
mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Chill for 30 minutes (the mixture will be sticky).
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in confectioners' sugar.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving. Store in refrigerator.

title: shrimp creole(serves 6)
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic until tender.
Add tomatoes, sauce, salt, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and hot sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and cold water and stir into sauce.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes longer.
Serve over hot rice.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together. Add eggs, vanilla and salt and beat until well blended.
Place crust on a cookie sheet and pour in filling.
Drop dollops of melted chocolate chips on top of filling and swirl with a knife like a marble cake.
Bake on the cookie sheet for about 25 to 30 minutes or until clean knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.
Chill 3 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pasta tuna salad
directions: Mix together tuna, chopped boiled eggs, mayonnaise, celery seed and cooked shell macaroni.
Mix carefully so that you do not tear the macaroni shells.
Fold in the drained green peas.
Serve cold.

title: milk dud dessert
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar and beat again.
Mix together rusk crumbs, nuts, vanilla and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Melt Milk Duds, milk, confectioners sugar and butter until smooth, stirring constantly.
Let stand until cool and creamy.
Whip the cream; spread over baked portion. Pour sauce on top and refrigerate overnight.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake according to box directions.
Frost with canned cream cheese frosting or make cream cheese frosting yourself.

title: crazy cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.	Put all dry ingredients into pan
and
mix.
Make 3 small holes in this mixture.
Into hole 1, put the vanilla.
Into hole 2, put the vinegar.
Into hole 3,
put the oil.
Pour 1 cup water over all the ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice	with your favorite icing or serve with whipped topping.

title: vanilla chip fruit tart
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy. Blend in flour.
Press onto 12-inch round pizza pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Stir and let sit for 10 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening until size of a pea.
Add buttermilk; add yeast dissolved in lukewarm water.
Stir in flour until dampened.
Knead 8 to 10 times on floured surface.
Roll out and cut into biscuits. By leaving space between them, they will brown better.
Brush with butter.
Let rise approximately 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Dough can be stored in tightly covered bowl in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Yield: 50 biscuits.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, peas, almonds, bacon and chopped eggs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix mayonnaise and Ranch powder together and spread on top of salad mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Best if made the night before.

title: lasagna
directions: Spray 9
x
12-inch baking dish with Pam.
Spread 1 cup tomato sauce
on
bottom.
Layer
with
noodles,
breaking off excess length.
Cover
with
1 1/2 cups tomato sauce, 1 cup of tofu mixture
(tofu,
onion, green peppers, yeast flakes, salt and basil,
crumbled)
and 1 cup CASHEW CHEESE.
Repeat layer. For third
layer,
end
with noodles, sauce, CASHEW CHEESE and tofu. Sprinkle on PARMESAN CHEESE.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Place all ingredients together in large 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Stir; add 1 cup of Velveeta cheese. Put back into oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: watergate salad or dessert
directions: Mix dry pudding and Cool Whip until pudding is dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple and juice.
Mix well.
Add marshmallows and pecans.
Refrigerate for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving. Made the night before is better.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage strata
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown sausage; drain well.
Brown onions.
Warm up soup.
Combine with milk and eggs.
Tear bread in small chunks to cover pan well.
Alternate with bread, cheese and sausage.
Pour combined liquid over.
Can be made ahead.
Great for brunch.
Bake in 325° oven 45 minutes.
Check doneness with toothpick.

title: lucille's pickles
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
In a large bowl with lid, put remaining ingredients.
Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Seal with lids for one hour at room temperature.
Put in jars with lids and keep in refrigerator.
Wait 10 days before eating.
They will keep for a year or longer.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: eggs-ham brunch
directions: Butter a 3-quart Pyrex dish.
Remove crust and butter both sides of 8 slices very thin bread.
Layer 8 slices ham, then 8 slices cheese.
Repeat with same second layer.
Then beat eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over casserole.
Refrigerate 24 hours (or freeze for several weeks).
One hour before cooking, saute 1 cup crushed Bacon Thins in 1 stick butter.
Sprinkle over top of egg dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 12.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Sprinkle a few tablespoons of flour over nuts, cherries and raisins.
Cream shortening, sugar and add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and nuts, cherries and raisins. Add hot applesauce.
Grease and flour a tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cake is similar to a fruit cake. Place cool cake in a tin for about 1 week before serving.
Freezes well.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add raw peanuts and salt.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add soda; stir well.
Pour on buttered pan.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix dough (flour, powder, salt, sugar, shortening and milk). Roll into a rectangle.
Cover with a thick layer of apples. Roll up as for cinnamon rolls and slice off.
Arrange in casserole and cover with a syrup made of the brown sugar and water.
Heat brown sugar and water to boiling, then pour over mixture in casserole. Sprinkle on cinnamon.
Bake until a delicate brown in a 350° oven.

title: black bean and salsa salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine first five ingredients.
Mix well. Blend the S & W ready cut salsa and the dressing pour over salad and toss well.
Cover and chill.
Spoon into lettuce leaves. Makes 8 servings.

title: spicy shrimp with artichokes
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add artichokes and cook, stirring occasionally, 2 minutes.
Add shrimp, increase heat to high and cook, stirring 2 to 3 minutes or until shrimp are pink and loosely curled.
Add water, wine, chicken stock base and rice mixes.
Heat to boiling over high heat; boil 1 minute.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Stir in red peppers, scallions and green beans.
Cook over medium-low heat 5 to 8 minutes longer, or until rice is tender and beans are cooked through.
Serve immediately.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Mix peas, green beans, celery, onions and pimento.
Salt to taste and let stand while mixing salad oil, sugar, vinegar, water and paprika.
Shake in a jar until mixed real good.
Pour over vegetables and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: salmon quiche
directions: Cut chilled butter into flour.
Stir in water to form pastry. Roll between waxed paper to desired thickness.
Place in 10-inch quiche pie pan.
Flute edges.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour well; add eggs and butter.
Mix well. Add coarsely chopped nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Great served with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: banana split cake
directions: Blend 1 stick margarine with graham cracker crumbs.
Line bottom of 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan with this crust.

title: scottish oatcakes
directions: Mix flour, oats, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add water, mixing with fork.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out into rounds (with glass).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until golden brown (about 20 to 25 minutes).

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter. Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine with Cheez Whiz, vegetables and soup.
Fold in cooked rice.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bear roast
directions: Rub roast with garlic and pepper.
Place roast in a crock-pot or slow-cooker.
Combine soup mix and stewed tomatoes.
Pour over roast.
Cook on low for 6 to 7 hours.

title: apple raisin cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Let stand 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
After 1 hour, add flour, soda, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg and salt.
Mix well.
Add margarine, vanilla, eggs and raisins.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy vegetable-noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Heat vegetables in microwave just until warmed.
Drain both and place into a sealable bowl.
Pour over that, 1/2 bottle of the dressing and toss to mix.
Chill. Before serving, toss and you may want to add a little more dressing, if desired.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use a teaspoon to a cup of boiling water.

title: vegetable beef barley soup
directions: Place meat, tomatoes, salt and bay leaf in a medium saucepan. Add 2 cups water, cover and bring to a boil.
Skim surface, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add bean, corn, onion, barley, oregano and garlic.
Simmer 1 hour or longer until tender.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown ground beef; stir in cheese and chili.
Serve in fondue pot with chips.

title: cream potatoes
directions: Partially thaw the hash browns.
Melt butter and pour half over the hash browns in baking pan.
Mix in all other ingredients except corn flakes.
Mix corn flakes and the other
half of the melted butter. Spread on top of potato mixture. Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.

title: spinach pies
directions: Saute the garlic in olive oil.
Roll dough into 4 circles. Mix the spinach, garlic and black olives to make the filling. Place filling on 1/2 of each dough circle and top with provolone cheese and pepperoni, if desired.
Fold dough over filling to make turnover.

title: lavender sachets
directions: Yields 4 ounces or enough to fill four sachets.

title: tomato soup spice cake
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 3 ingredients.
Combine soup and water.
Sift soda, flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to mixture.
Bake in greased 9 1/2 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until tester comes clean.

title: butterhorns
directions: Stir the warm water and yeast to dissolve.
Stir in the milk, salt, shortening, sugar, eggs and half the flour.
Mix with spoon until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to handle easily.
Mix with hands.
Knead until smooth.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double.
Roll dough scarcely 1/4-inch thick into a 12-inch circle.
Spread with butter.
Cut into 16 pie shaped pieces. Beginning at rounded edge, roll up.
Place on pan, point underneath.
For excellent eating and keeping quality, keep dough as soft as possible, almost sticky, just so you are able to handle them.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Beat the egg and add the milk.
Peel and slice the cucumbers, and dip them into the cracker crumbs.
Lay the cucumbers out to dry a little, then dip them into the egg-milk mixture and then again into the cracker crumbs.
Fry them in butter or vegetable oil, and sprinkle them with salt to taste.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Dice up potatoes and tomatoes. Empty juice from all cans of vegetables, except the tomatoes and mixed vegetables.
Add meat, onion, salt and pepper (to taste). Simmer 35 to 45 minutes.
May cook longer, if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add pimento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and seasoning.
Mix well and chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans or parsley.

title: three layer strawberry salad
directions: Mix and pack in 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: potato-onion soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add diced potatoes.
Add just enough water to cover.
Cook until potatoes are tender and liquid has cooked down low.
Add milk; stir and cook until hot.
Do not boil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with saltine crackers.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in clear glass container.
Cover with mayonnaise dressing.
Garnish with quartered boiled eggs or Parmesan cheese. May add any other desired vegetables.

title: the peddler's marinated chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken breasts in a shallow glass casserole dish.
Mix well.
Add chicken breasts, making sure marinade sauce covers breasts.
Allow to marinate in refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours.
Cook on real charcoal or gas grill.
Serves up to 12 people.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine in iron skillet the corn syrup, sugar and water. Stir until sugar dissolves and cooks to 234° or soft ball on candy thermometer.

Add raw peanuts and boil to 310° or brittle stage. Remove from heat and add baking soda, vanilla, salt and butter. (These should be mixed in a cup before you begin and mix up so can be added all at once.)
Cool and break into pieces.

title: tomato soup
directions: In medium saucepan, cook and stir onion in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in cream cheese.
Gradually stir in soup and milk; beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Add seasoning.
Heat, stirring frequently, but do not boil.
If desired, garnish each serving with sieved egg yolk.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: pineapple oatmeal drops
directions: Turn undrained pineapple into 9-inch skillet.
Simmer over medium-high heat, about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until pineapple measures 1 1/4 cups.
Stir frequently toward end of cooking to avoid scorching.
Resift flour with next 4 ingredients. Cream shortening with sugars until fluffy; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in molasses and vanilla, then flour mixture.
Add pineapple, oats and walnuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake in center of 350° oven until lightly browned, about 13 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: peanut buster parfait
directions: Combine crushed cookies and melted margarine together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
When frozen, spread softened ice cream over crust, add Spanish peanuts and freeze again.
Boil sugar, margarine, canned milk and chocolate chips. Cook until thick.
Cool and spread on ice cream and nuts. Sprinkle more nuts over top and freeze again.

title: waffle rosettes
directions: Beat eggs slightly, then add sugar slowly.
Now add milk.
Mix well.
Add flour and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla. Using your deep fryer, heat waffle iron in oil, then dip in batter and then back in oil until brown.
Knock off of iron onto paper towel.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: classic green bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Add beans and 1/2 can of the onions.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake well.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: angel surprise
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, stirring thoroughly until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries.
While thawing, stir often. When it begins to congeal, put into large bowl and beat with mixer until light and foamy.
Cut or break cake into small pieces and fold into jello mixture.
Pour into large angel food cake pan and place in refrigerator until set.
Remove from pan and slice.
Top with whipped cream and powdered sugar mixture.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine dressing and butter.
Sprinkle 1/2 dressing (dry mix) over bottom of a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish or pan.
Place squash on top of dressing.
Sprinkle grated carrots over top.
Combine the soup and sour cream; spread over the carrots.
Top with the remaining dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Melt chocolate almond bark and dip balls into mix until coated.
Place on waxed paper until set.

title: chicken with a kick
directions: Combine bread crumbs and taco seasoning.
Run chicken under water or spray with Pam.
Coat it in the bread crumb mixture.
On each chicken breast, layer 1 stick of cheese and a spoonful of green chillies.
Salt, if desired.
Roll the breast, tucking the ends in, and secure with a toothpick.
Drizzle 2 teaspoons of margarine over each roll.
Sprinkle remaining bread crumb mixture on chicken.
Place the chicken, seam side up, in an ungreased baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.
Uncover and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove toothpicks and serve.

title: my own cornbread, upside down
directions: Brown ground beef; add all other ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix cornmeal, buttermilk and shortening.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine. Press into 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Let cool.

title: congealed salad
directions: Place Jell-O and pineapple in saucepan and boil.
remove from heat.
Let cool.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Add pecans. Pour in Pyrex dish or salad mold.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in oven in a deep dish.
Beat together the sugar, flour and milk to a smooth batter.
Pour over melted margarine; do not stir.
Empty fruit and liquid from fruit over the batter and sprinkle with 1/2 cup of sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Batter will rise to the top.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Place washed shrimp in 3-quart baking dish.
Melt butter and mix with seasonings.
Pour over shrimp and cover.
Cook in microwave 4 minutes at a time.
Stir and cook again.
Keep up process until shells separate slightly from shrimp.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix mustard, flour and salt.
Pound dry ingredients into steak, covering both sides.
Brown in oil on both sides.
Cover meat with onion and tomatoes.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce, salt and brown sugar over all.
Cover pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rolled beef steak with italian stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except steak
and stewed tomatoes, until moist.
Spread mixture on steak and roll up.
Tie or pin meat. Brown on both sides.
Add the stewed tomatoes.
Put in a covered roaster; cook for 2 hours at 350°.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in eggs, molasses and vinegar. Add flour, soda, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix ingredients until blended.
Form dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 12 minutes at 325°.
As the ball melts down during baking, the cookie develops the characteristic crinkled surface.

title: horseradish rolls
directions: Drain sauerkraut thoroughly. Mix well softened cream cheese. Season to taste with garlic and horseradish.
Separate beef slices. Place 1 tsp. mixture on beef. Roll tightly. Refrigerate 4 hours. May be cut in bite sizes.

title: spiced cranberries
directions: Put cloves and cinnamon in a cheesecloth bag.
Combine these with sugar, water and vinegar and boil 5 minutes.
Add cranberries.
Cook until skins pop.
Refrigerate.
Leave spices in until serving time.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks.
Add salt and soda to flour. Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream to butter and egg mixture; add vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until done in tube pan.
Let cool 10 minutes and remove immediately.
Be sure and flour and grease pan.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: venison saute
directions: Saute veggies in oil until soft.
Brown meat in oil.
Add veggies, bouillon and spices.
Simmer, uncovered, 35 to 45 minutes.
Add red wine after 30 minutes and simmer to reduce liquid.
Serve with brown or white rice.

title: autumn evening supper
directions: Combine potatoes, chopped cheese, onion slices, dressing and pimento.
Spoon into an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with sausage.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated.
Top with 3 slices of cheese cut in 1/2 diagonally.
Continue baking until processed cheese begins to melt.
Yields 6 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except sour cream.
Pour half of the mixture in casserole.
Let congeal.
Spread sour cream over mixture and pour remaining mixture over this.
Congeal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion in salted water until tender; drain. In saucepan, melt the butter, blend in the flour, salt and pepper. Add milk and cook until bubbly stirring constantly.
Reduce heat. Blend in the cream cheese until smooth.
Place well drained vegetables in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over top.
Mix lightly.
Top with the cheese.
Melt the 2 tablespoons butter; toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix in other ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven until done.

title: cola salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Let the mixture cool.
Add Coca-Cola and let start to jell.
Add pineapple, cherries and marshmallows.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: Mix boiling water and bran together; let stand.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
To this add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add the All-Bran and buttermilk.

title: lora's cornbread
directions: Add buttermilk until the mixture is the consistency of cake batter.
Bake in large skillet at 450° until brown.

title: mints
directions: Mix and knead like dough.
May need a little more 10x sugar. Add a little coloring.
Roll in small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Press into mold.
Unmold at once on wax paper.
Let set several days, uncovered, before eating.

title: spiced mixed nuts
directions: In large skillet, melt butter and stir in golden onion recipe soup mix thoroughly blended with sugar and cumin.
Add nuts and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until nuts are thoroughly coated with soup mixture and golden brown. Serve warm or spread nuts on baking sheet to cool.
Store in airtight container up to 2 weeks.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: very quick beef stew
directions: If more juice is needed, add a can of consomme or 1 cup beef bouillon.

title: beef stew with dumplings
directions: Wipe meat with damp cloth.
Cut in cubes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and dredge in flour.
Cut off the fat and fry out in frying pan.
Add meat and stir constantly in order to sear the surface.
When nicely browned, put in saucepan.
Cover well with boiling water and let boil for 10 minutes, then cook at simmering temperature for about 3 hours.
Add more water if necessary during cooking.
Add vegetables during last hour of cooking and thicken with 2 tablespoons of flour rubbed smooth with a little cold water.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place sliced potatoes into 9 x 11 casserole dish.
Arrange pork chops over potatoes.
Combine the soups and pour over the pork chops and potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: granny caddell's brunswick stew
directions: Cut up onion and stew about 10 minutes.
Dump all other ingredients together and simmer a few minutes and you're ready to eat.

title: sandra's frosting
directions: Mix together milk and pudding mix (mix normally calls for 2 cups).
Chill pudding in refrigerator.
In separate mixing bowl, blend together the butter, Crisco and sugar.
When pudding is cool, mix together with other ingredients.
Be sure not to undermix.
Frosting should be light and fluffy.
Vanilla and chocolate pudding work best.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and set aside, then combine soup, mustard, milk and onions.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, then layer the potatoes and sauce mix over the hot dogs.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable seasoning blend
directions: Combine and store in airtight containers.
Use to season vegetables as desired.

title: brer rabbit blackberry cobbler
directions: Toss slightly sweetened berries with 1 tablespoon flour to coat.
Place berries in a lightly greased deep baking dish.
In a bowl, combine 1 cup flour, salt, butter and milk; blend well.
Pat dough out into thin strips and arrange as crust over berries.
In a saucepan, combine sugar and water; bring to a boil and boil until sugar dissolves.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until crust is golden brown.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Crush wafers with Nestle Quik and butter; press into pan and chill well.
Stir to dissolve marshmallows in scalded milk.
Cool to room temperature.
Add both liqueurs and fold in whipped cream. Pour into chilled crust; put in freezer for 2 hours.

title: day ahead - mashed potatoes
directions: Put potatoes into large pot, cover with water.
Bring to boil and simmer over medium heat until tender.
Drain.
Put potatoes in large mixing bowl; beat with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Beat in butter and cream cheese, which have been cut into mall pieces.
Beat in sour cream, salt and pepper.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
Add 1 litre of ginger ale to each 1/2 gallon of juice when ready to use, in large punch bowl.

title: hearty meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix and combine all ingredients except the meat loaf sauce. Bake uncovered one hour, remove from oven and drain. Top with meat loaf sauce, bake an additional 10-15 minutes. Allow to stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well by hand.
Roll in balls.
Bake about 10 minutes at 425°.

title: annette's blackberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water in heavy pan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat; add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Gently stir in berries.
Simmer on low heat 5 minutes.
Pour into pie shell. Chill until firm.
Top with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: babka(polish bread)
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour from total amount.
Mix together flour, rapid rise yeast and all other dry ingredients in large pot. Heat butter and milk to 125° to 130°.
Stir warm liquids into dry mixture.
Add eggs and extra flour, kneading and mixing until it stops sticking to fingers.
(You may need extra flour.)
Squeeze water from raisins and knead raisins into dough.
Cover, let rise 10 minutes.
Put into greased loaf pans.
Let rise in warm oven until doubled, then bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 loaves.

title: bean and sausage casserole
directions: Combine beans in 2 1/2-quart dish, after draining them.
Brown sausage in a skillet and drain.
While sausage browns add beef broth, tomato sauce, cumin, salt, pepper and picante sauce to beans.
Saute garlic and onions and add them and the sausage to the beans.
Cover and bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Serves 6 people. 419 calories, 3 grams fat.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix; mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Flatten with fork for design.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Do not overbake.
Cool.
Store, covered, at room temperature.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: old-fashioned chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven.
Add water and 1 teaspoon salt. Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and let cool slightly.
Bone chicken and set aside.

title: scallion butter burgers
directions: Combine meat, salt, celery seed and scallions.
Shape into 6 patties.
Press pepper into surface of patties.
Grill.
Toast rye bread and spread with Scallion Butter.
Place hamburgers on toasted rye bread.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over margarine, Crisco, sugar and salt. Melt
and
cool.
Stir
in eggs and yeast that has been dissolved in
the warm water.
Add flour; work in well.
Store in refrigerator
for 4 hours before using.
Make out rolls and let stand 3 hours before baking, in a 350° oven.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: sabrina b. lamb's lasagna
directions: Cook hamburger; drain and add spaghetti sauce, touch of garlic powder and black pepper and simmer.
Mix cottage cheese and Ricotta cheese and put in refrigerator.
Cook lasagna for 9 minutes and drain.
Run cold water over it and leave in pan.
Put a layer of sauce (1 or 2 cups) in bottom of baking pan.
Then a layer of noodles, then another layer of sauce, then a layer of cottage cheese.
Repeat layers until all is used.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: cauliflower and cheese salad
directions: Combine cauliflower pieces, bacon and cheese in large bowl. Blend dressing ingredients and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over salad; toss thoroughly.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: steam pudding
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a bread pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with sauce.
(This can be steamed in a coffee can also; will be more moist.)

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.	Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine potatoes with 1/4 cup melted butter and add sour cream, soup, onion, cheese and seasonings.
Mix well and pour into lightly greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
In separate bowl mix cornflake crumbs and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Top potato mixture with cornflake mixture and cover with foil.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and bake uncovered for an additional 20 minutes.
Serves large group.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices. Combine flour, salt and pepper. Dredge tomato slices in flour. Saute in hot shortening until brown on both sides. Cook until soft in middle. Serve hot.

title: cocoa-cola salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries thoroughly.
Combine juices and bring to boiling.
Dissolve jello in juice and cool to the consistency of egg whites.
Place cherries, pineapple and nuts in layers in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Crumble cream cheese over top. Add coke to jello and mix well.
Pour over fruit and lift with fork gently so jello covers bottom of dish.
Chill until set.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour; brown in oleo.
Add soup and water. Simmer until done.

title: mexican rice
directions: In saucepan, saut garlic and onion with the olive oil until they are tender.
Add stewed tomatoes, broth, picante sauce, chili powder, cumin and sea salt.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and water.
Cover and reduce heat to a simmer.
Simmer about 20 minutes or until the liquid is absorbed.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain well.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish and dot with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons oleo until tender. Combine in bowl with chicken and chilies; set aside. In same pan, melt 3 tablespoons oleo. Blend in flour and salt. Stir in broth; cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese. Stir half mixture into chicken.

Dip each tortilla into remaining sauce; fill with 1/4 cup chicken, then roll up. Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Pour remaining sauce over top. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind and drain first 3 ingredients.
Mix together sugar, vinegar, salt and turmeric.
Boil 3 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: churros
directions: Mix the water, salt and 1 tablespoon of oil in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Put it in a bowl and mix well with the flour. Put it into balls.
Put the balls into hot, deep oil inside a frying pan.
When crispy, take out and cover with sugar.
Enjoy!

title: sour cream chocolate frosting
directions: Mix butter and chocolate (melted) thoroughly.
Blend in sugar. Stir in sour cream.
Beat until fluffy and of good spreading consistency.

title: bread
directions: Dissolve sugar; add
1 package yeast and stir once.
Let yeast foam.
Add flour and dried milk, alternately, one cup at a time. Add enough flour to make consistency of bread dough.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Sprinkle the strawberries with a little of the sugar.
Whisk the oil and eggs together just a little, then pour over strawberries and stir together.
Combine and mix all the dry ingredients together except the nuts.
Pour the strawberry mixture into the flour mixture and blend by hand thoroughly.
Fold in the nuts, if desired.
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch buttered and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool completely before serving.
Serve sprinkled with powdered sugar and sliced.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 8 biscuits.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Prepare chocolate instant pudding according to directions on box. Place into back of plastic dump truck or plastic sand pail. Sprinkle crushed Oreos over top of pudding. Use gummy worms to place in dirt pudding as if worms are crawling out of the dirt. Yields 10 to 12. Good for birthday parties.

title: wieners and beans
directions: Cut wieners in small circles and add to other ingredients.
Mix and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350°, covered, about 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook 10 minutes, until wieners are just beginning to brown.
Serve with a salad, French fries or macaroni and cheese and garlic bread.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mash sweet potatoes with butter.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and eggs and stir well.
Stir in milk, nutmeg and flavorings.
Beat at high speed on electric mixer for three minutes.
Add coconut.
Pour into two 9-inch pie shells and bake one hour or one hour and fifteen minutes, until set.

title: ruthie's cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except one cup pecans.
Form into a ball and roll mixture in remaining pecans.
Cover with foil and refrigerate until served.
Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: green-herb dressing
directions: In blender, process the cottage cheese until very smooth. Transfer to a medium bowl.
Whisk in the yogurt, Sap Sago or Parmesan cheese, lemon juice, honey, mustard, shallots, basil and black pepper.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper.
Drain grease. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix ground beef, egg and seasonings.
Break bread into small crumbs and put in bowl. Knead all together by hand and pack together to form a loaf shape. Place in an ungreased loaf pan.
Cover with aluminum foil and place in oven for approximately 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes. Test for doneness.

title: pasta with clam sauce
directions: Drain clams.
Reserve liquid.
In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute 2 minutes.
Add reserved clam liquid, wine, basil and pepper.
Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in clams and heat 1 minute.
Toss pasta with clam sauce and parsley.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Makes 5 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli into flowerets.
Drain well.
Mix broccoli, cheese, onion and bacon.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar to make dressing.
Just before serving, toss salad with dressing.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, cook onions in margarine until tender. Add remaining ingredients; stir over low heat until cheese is melted and mixture is hot.
Serve.

title: fish stew for 2
directions: Peel onion and potatoes; dice. Place 2 to 3-quart pot on burner; heat.
Add diced bacon, brown.
Add water, potatoes and onion.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add salmon after bone is removed and broken into small pieces.
Heat to boiling, add seasoning and eggs, one at a time; add catsup.
Cook over medium heat until eggs are done.

title: sue's graham crackers
directions: Line cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Bring margarine, butter and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add chopped nuts. Spread over graham crackers and cook at 300° for 12 minutes. Remove from oven and put on wax paper.
Cool and eat.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Boil sausage for 20 minutes (cool).
Next, brown ground beef and skin sausage.
Drain well to remove grease.
Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan as follows:
some sauce, noodles, meat mixture, cheese slices.
Sprinkle with oregano and basil.
Repeat until all items are used (I usually layer twice).
Top layer with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: my favorite egyptian yellow chicken with almonds
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Heat 3/4 of the oil in a pan and lightly saute the garlic and almonds.
Add turmeric, stir into the hot oil and garlic.
Add chicken and brown on both sides.
Sprinkle in the parsley and pour in the water or stock.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and shake or beat well.
Add about a teaspoon or so of catsup to give it some color.

title: holly
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Mix in vanilla and food coloring.
Pour over corn flakes.
Mix until cereal is coated.

title: chicken breasts with champagne
directions: Heat butter in a skillet.
Add chicken and brown on both sides.
Remove chicken to a 4-quart casserole, reserving drippings in skillet.
Add mushrooms to skillet and saute; remove mushrooms and set aside.
Stir champagne into drippings in skillet; simmer until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Pour over chicken; cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove chicken to platter, reserving liquid.
Add sour cream, salt and pepper to reserved liquid; whisk until smooth. Pour over chicken and top with mushrooms.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: In plastic bag, mix oil and soup, then put potatoes in bag and put tie on it.
Shake them up.
Preheat oven to 450°; bake in jelly roll pan, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
Spray pan with Pam.

title: quick fruit salad(cooking for  a crowd)
directions: Combine all ingredients except bananas.
Chill until ready to serve.
Just before serving, fold in bananas.
Makes 100 servings.

title: debbie's shrimp ball
directions: Mix cream cheese with shrimp.
Smash together and form into a ball in a bowl.
Pour cocktail sauce over ball and serve with crackers.
Garnish with shrimp, if desired.

title: 12 to 24 hour salad
directions: Use 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: jelly muffins
directions: Set oven at 425° for a hot oven.
Grease the muffin pan with shortening.
Sift the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into a mixing bowl.
Mix the beaten egg, milk and cooking oil.
Add the egg and milk mixture to dry ingredients.
Fill the greased muffin pans 1/2 full.
Push 1 teaspoon jelly into each muffin.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: no carb cheese chips
directions: Heat nonstick griddle to even medium heat. USE NO OIL OR SPRAY. Recommend first batch be approximately 3 chips. Using 3-inch diameter "pie" shaped cheese, place on griddle. Grill cheese until edges turn brown. Using small sharp-edged spatula, flip chips over. After approximately 2 minutes, press with spatula and remove to a paper towel-lined plate. The chips become crisp as they cool. Practice makes perfect! Refrigerate and store in Ziploc bags.

title: cream soup
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil to soften vegetables. Add milk and butter and bring to a simmer.
Then add milk that has the flour added to it.
Stir until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Serve and enjoy!

title: strawberry melon salad
directions: In a bowl, combine yogurt, oil, honey, vinegar and ginger. Mix well.
Some strawberries can be sliced gently into mixture. Arrange melon slices and strawberries around dip.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Mix 1/2 cake mix (dry), butter, brown sugar, water and eggs until smooth.
Stir in rest of cake mix and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Spread marshmallows on the top and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Heat frosting and drizzle over warm cake.

title: zuppa di cavolo(cabbage soup)
directions: In a bowl, soak the beans in water to cover for 12 hours. Drain and set aside.
Remove and discard the hard stalks from the cabbage leaves.
Slice the leaves roughly; set aside.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, brown sugar, egg and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheet. Dip bottom of small greased glass into granulated sugar and press cookie flat.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack. Makes 5 dozen.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Place drained pineapple chunks in baking pan.
Mix together sugar and flour.
Sprinkle over pineapple.
Place cheese over sugar and flour. Mix crackers and butter until blended.
Spread cracker mixture over cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbling.

title: baked salmon
directions: Simmer celery, add tomato paste and pour over bread.
Saute onions and mix in paste.
Stuff salmon.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: mom's baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions and drain.
Stir in butter until melted and mixed throughout spaghetti.
Put one-third of spaghetti in a large buttered casserole or deep baking dish.
Top with dots of butter and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover spaghetti with broken pieces of cheese.

Pour tomato sauce on cheese, sprinkle with italian seasoning and Parmesan cheese. Repeat layers two more times, end with crushed tomatoes on top. Sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper, top with more Parmesan.
Bake at 350. degrees for one hour or until top is golden and edges are bubbly.
Cool for 10 minutes before serving.
Serve 6 to 8.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Score cucumber lengthwise with fork; slice thin.
In a medium bowl, combine vinegar and water.
Add cucumber slices.
Let stand at room temperature at least 30 minutes; drain well.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make vanilla pudding according to directions on box; set aside.
Slice bananas into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with a layer of vanilla wafers.
Mix Eagle Brand milk with Cool Whip and mix well.
Fold into pudding mixture.
Pour over the cookies and bananas.
Top with cookie crumbs.
Put cookies around edge of dish for decoration, if desired.

title: pizza treat(easy for children to make.)
directions: Flatten bread with a rolling pin.
Mix oregano and garlic powder with tomato sauce. Spread on flattened bread. Top with green pepper, mushrooms and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 1.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, pumpkin, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed one minute.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Beat one minute at medium speed.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch round pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove.
Cool completely.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In a medium bowl beat the butter and cocoa until the butter is softened.
Gradually add the powdered sugar, beating well.
Slowly beat in the milk and vanilla.
Slowly beat in second half of powdered sugar and additional milk, if needed, to make spreading consistency.

title: chicken alfredo casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite size pieces. Cook pasta until done. Place drained pasta in a 13x9 in. casserole dish. Add cut up chicken. Warm alfredo sauce and pour onto pasta and chicken. Mix together. Sprinkle seasoning on top to taste.

title: jam cake
directions: My grandmother used to make this before Christmas and I have such fond memories of watching her prepare meals and baked goods in her kitchen.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, put in the milk and butter. Place in oven at 350° until the rest of the ingredients are ready. Combine the biscuits, eggs, raisins, nuts, sugar, allspice and vanilla. Add to milk mixture. Stir well and put in oven and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop stems fine.
Soak bread in a little water or milk and squeeze dry.
Mix together chopped stems, bread, garlic, parsley, eggs, Ricotta, salt and pepper. Fill each mushroom cap with stuffing.
Arrange stuffed mushrooms in a baking pan greased with olive oil.
Drizzle a little olive oil over mushrooms and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Contains 2 mushrooms per serving.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Combine berries, sugar, lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon in 1-quart baking dish.
Combine oats, brown sugar, flour and remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon in a small bowl.
Cut in butter and sprinkle over fruit.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes until topping is brown and fruit is bubbly.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: onion salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
When it begins to set, add the mayonnaise, celery, green onions and cottage cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Put cracker crumbs on top.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl, make a well in center of the mixture.
Add Eggs, Buttermilk and Shortening.
Stir just enough to moisten ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to use, as long as five to six weeks. When ready to bake, spoon batter into greased muffin tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350 for 20 minutes.
Yields 5-1/2 dozen.

title: tandoori chicken
directions: Clean and skin chicken.
Cut into required pieces and wash it. Drain water completely.
Apply lime juice and salt to taste and keep it aside for 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot bean supreme
directions: Combine beans and undrained pork and beans in a crock-pot. Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain.
Stir into bean mixture.
Add catsup and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: taake pumpkin bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add pumpkin; stir well.
Mix soda and spices together.
Stir into pumpkin mix.
Add flour and water alternately.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into two 1-pound greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and refrigerate for moisture.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix well cream cheese and shrimp.
Mix well catsup, horseradish, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over shrimp mixture when ready to serve.

title: mom's harvest loaf cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then add pumpkin, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Mix together.
Batter will be thick.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes (tube pan or loaf pan).

title: cheesy mexican hush puppies
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg and milk.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Mix broth and ginger root.
Bring to boil, remove ginger root. Stir in eggs; remove from heat.
Garnish with scallions and serve.

title: whole wheat batter bread
directions: Add yeast to warm water; stir.
Add honey; stir.
Add oleo, salt, white flour and 1/2 cup wheat flour.
Beat on low speed until blended.
Then on high speed for 1 minute.
Stir in remaining wheat flour.
Cover and let rise until double, about 45 minutes.
Grease 1 loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: individual pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place hamburger in skillet.
Brown and drain.
Add tomato sauce, oregano, salt and garlic salt.
Pat out each biscuit on cookie sheet to form pizza crust.
Spread each biscuit with hamburger mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and put in casserole.
Crush one package of Ritz crackers.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter and mix together.
Crumble over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water.
While hot, add butter or margarine and let melt.
Add chopped onion to squash and butter mixture.
When cool, add the following ingredients and mix thoroughly:
sour cream, chicken soup and celery soup.
Line bottom of oblong dish with buttered corn bread crumbs (plenty).
Pour squash mixture over corn bread crumbs and top with more buttered cornbread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Watch carefully so it doesn't get too brown.

title: any fruit coffeecake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until creamy.
Add next 4 ingredients. Spread 2/3 of the batter in jelly roll pan (well-greased).
Spread pie filling over batter.
Drop remaining batter by tablespoonfuls onto pie filling.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: robin's yum-yum salad
directions: Put gelatin soaking in water.
Cook sugar, lemon juice and pineapple to boil, then add gelatin and bring to another boil. Cool. Combine Cool Whip to mixture in a large bowl and add grated cheese.
Place mixture in flat 1-quart casserole dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: party rolls
directions: Mix butter, Worcestershire sauce, poppy seed, mustard and onion.
Refrigerate until spreadable.
Slice rolls in half. Place ham and cheese on bottom half.
Spread butter mixture on top. Wrap tray well in aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This will make 2 trays of party rolls.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruits.
Add mayonnaise and a little sugar.
Mash the cream cheese and mayonnaise together with fruits.
Save 1/4 cup of pineapple juice.
Combine the gelatine to pour over the mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: meaty turnovers(makes 4 servings)
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 375°. Separate dough into triangles and place 4 of the triangles on a greased cookie sheet.
Spread Ham, Chicken or Tuna Filling about 1/4 inch from edges of triangles.

title: pecan loaf cake
directions: Mix thoroughly, flouring fruit with some of given flour.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 to 40 minutes.
May use a 12 x 9 x 2-inch loaf pan or 10-inch tube pan (greased and floured).

title: ham casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Cut zucchini very thin.
Mix with salt into a dishpan or small basin.
Bury in ice.
Cover with plate and weight down.
Let stand 2 hours; drain.
Add sugar, turmeric, cloves, celery seed, mustard seed, vinegar and water.
Heat to scalding point (do not boil).
Fill jars.
Put liquid in jars to 1/4 from top.
Put hot lids on and seal.
Put in refrigerator and chill 2 days before using.

title: crustless sweet potato pineapple pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, eggs, sugar and milk.
Beat until blended and smooth.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Stir in crumbs.
Grease a deep 9-inch pie pan; pour filling in pan.
Bake in a preheated oven for 45 to 55 minutes at 325° or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool and refrigerate; top with whipped cream or topping.
Cut in wedges and serve.

title: doughnut balls
directions: Mix sugar, milk, eggs and shortening.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; add nutmeg.
Combine the 2 mixtures and add the coconut.
Drop by teaspoon into deep hot fat.
Fry until brown. When cool, roll in powdered sugar (optional).
Bake at 375°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples thin and arrange in 8-inch square pan.
Combine dry ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Drizzle melted butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: country scrambled eggs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have ingredients ready.
Scramble eggs just barely done.
Top with grated cheese, ham or bacon, tomatoes, mushrooms and avocado.
Bake a few minutes in oven or microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: pancakes or waffles(with master mix)
directions: Blend ingredients.
Makes 18 medium-size pancakes or 6 waffles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, buttermilk, soda, and flour.
Mash ripe bananas with fork and add to the mixture.
Bake at 350° 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: e-z cheese cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and press in a pie pan.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter in large bowl of electric mixer; gradually beat in cheese and all other ingredients except flour.
Beat thoroughly, then gradually blend in flour.
Shape into four rolls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate several hours.

title: mashed potatoes with caramelized onions and cabbage
directions: Melt 1/2 of butter in large heavy skillet over medium heat. Add onions, cabbage and large pinch of salt. Cook until vegetables are deep brown, scraping bottom of pan frequently, about 40 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook potatoes until tender.
Add remaining butter and milk to potatoes and mash potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix one cup of onion mixture into potatoes. Mound potatoes in a shallow casserole.
Add vinegar and broth to remaining onion mixture.
Stir over high heat until liquid is almost evaporated.
Spoon onion mixture over potatoes.
Bake until very hot, about 20 minutes.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix the day before serving.
After mixed, dip will be thin; it will thicken overnight.
Any fruit can be used.
Sprinkle fruit with Fruit-Fresh to prevent from turning dark.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, blend soup and water.
Stir in macaroni and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Stir.
Top with bread crumbs and remaining cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and drain. Stir in salsa, corn, Miracle Whip and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of the meat mixture, chips and cheeses in 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers. Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes, if desired.

title: nutty apple muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, baking soda and nutmeg. In another bowl, beat eggs; add sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Stir in apples, nuts and coconut.
Stir in dry ingredients, just until moistened.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg and add sugar.
Add flour and salt.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Add baking powder.
Pour in greased baking pan and bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: striped delight
directions: *Or use 1 (6 serving size) package instant pudding and 2 1/2 cups cold milk.

title: strawberry banana shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth.

title: salt-cornstarch clay
directions: Mix salt and water in pan.
Simmer over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is well heated.
Remove from heat.
Add cornstarch and water.
Mix hard.
This will make a thick dough. Add food coloring if desired (or it can be left white and painted later).
Store in plastic bag in refrigerator.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
