directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Melt margarine; pour into 13 x 9 glass dish. Mix sugar with pretzels, then spread on top of margarine and pat down. Bake 8 to 10 minutes, then let cool.

title: party cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and beat. Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour batter into it and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar or to one's wish.

title: black forest cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box, stirring in cherry pie filling.
Divide into 2 or 3 well-greased round layer cake pans.
Bake as directed.
Check for doneness.
Let cake cool.

title: refritos-refried beans
directions: Cover the pintos with water and soak 1 1/2 hours or more. Cover with more water and cook, partially-covered, until well done, usually 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Make sure you check their water level periodically while they cook.
When they are soft, drain off excess water and mash well.
Heat butter or olive oil in skillet. Add onions, garlic, cumin and 1/2 tsp. salt.
Cook over low heat until onions are translucent.
Add green pepper, cover and simmer 5 to 8 minutes.
Add sauteed vegetables to the beans, along with 1 teaspoon salt and black pepper.
Mix well.
Add one cup grated cheese.

title: shrimp and grape salad
directions: Mix all except shrimp, grapes and nuts.
Let stand overnight. Mix all ingredients and serve on lettuce.

title: mama's meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup.
Form into 2-inch balls. Place in greased casserole dish; pour tomato soup over them.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: de-de's shrimp saute
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add shrimp, mushrooms, green pepper and garlic.
Saute until shrimp turn pink (3 to 5 minutes).

title: mud pie
directions: Mix together crushed Oreos and 1/3 cup melted butter; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Spread softened ice cream over cookie crust and freeze.
Melt chocolate and 2 tablespoons butter. Add sugar, salt and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Chill.
Spread over ice cream layer and freeze.
Whip cream and add Kahlua and powdered sugar.
Spread over chocolate layer; sprinkle with chopped nuts and return to freezer.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Brown and place in casserole dish.
Cut up onion and green pepper and place on top of meat.

title: fried wild turkey
directions: Slice turkey in small strips; soak in dressing for 4 to 5 hours.
Drain.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper.
Fry in oil until golden brown.

title: veggie soup
directions: Add the first 4 ingredients to the ground beef (browned and drained).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly for 2 or 3 hours.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Layer cheese on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine next four ingredients and pour half over the cheese.
Pour eggs over the cheese.
Pour remaining cream over the eggs.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: Pour oil in heavy skillet, then mix together hamburger, salt, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until hamburger is done.
Drain and set aside.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Mix with hamburger and cook on low heat until thickened.
Serve over mashed potatoes or rice.

title: baked ziti
directions: Mix ziti, Ricotta, Mozzarella, egg, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups sauce.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spread 1/2 cup sauce, then spoon macaroni mixture in and gently pat down with back of spoon.
Top with remaining 1 1/2 cups sauce; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting into squares.
Serve with additional sauce if desired.

title: peach pie
directions: Place peaches in bottom of 9 to 10-inch Pyrex pie plate. Remove crust from bread and cut into strips.
Place bread strips over peaches and make sure all peaches are covered.
Melt butter, mix with sugar, flour and egg.
Mix well and spoon over bread. Bake at 350° for 35 or 45 minutes until brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli or asparagus in a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch).
Top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk and pour over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, pumpkin, milk, egg yolks, spices and orange juice; cook until mix thickens.
Add gelatin to water and stir into hot mix.
Add beaten egg whites to 2 tablespoons sugar. Fold in pumpkin mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, undissolved yeast and salt.
Stir very warm water and oil into dry ingredients.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Cover; let rest for 10 minutes.
Oil a 14-inch pizza pan.
Roll dough to fit pan.
Top with your choice of fruit topping or pie filling.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes or until done.

title: pickled green pepper
directions: Wash pepper and remove seeds and insides.
Cut into slices. Put into pint jars and add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 cup water.
Add enough vinegar to cover pepper in jar.
Will pickle in about 2 weeks.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in oil.
Combine water, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce and pineapple juice.
Cook until thick.
Add meat.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add green pepper chunks, onion chunks and pineapple chunks.
Heat and serve over rice.

title: sour cream cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets until tender.
Meanwhile, combine soup, sour cream and onion flakes.
Cut potatoes in chunks and spread in the bottom of large pan.
Salt and pepper.
Spread mixture on top of potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in oven at 400° until cheese melts and is hot and bubbly.

title: tasty pork chops
directions: Spread chops in a baking dish and season with salt and pepper. Slice bell pepper and onion over top of pork chops.
Season with Worcestershire sauce and butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until desired doneness.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine soup, vinegar, sugar, oil and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to boil and pour over carrots.
Add onion and peppers.
Stir well.
Refrigerate overnight (covered).
Drain to serve as cold relish or heat as vegetable.
Keeps well for a long time in the refrigerator.

title: best ever caramels
directions: Combine sugars, corn syrup, cream, milk and butter.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally to firm ball stage (248°).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Cool.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Mix thickening with 2 tablespoons water until smooth.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples, sugar, flour and spices together.
Put mixture in unbaked crust.
Add milk and dots of butter.
Place strips or top crust on pie.
Bake in oven at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: pepsi cake
directions: Combine marshmallows, Pepsi-Cola, margarine and baking cocoa in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until marshmallows melt, stirring constantly.
Combine flour, sugar, eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla in large mixer bowl; mix well.
Add marshmallow mixture; beat well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Do not overbake.
Spread frosting over hot cake.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil or bake chicken breasts.
Cook, debone and break chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix together cream of chicken soup, sour cream and poppy seed, then with some water or broth.
Spray pan with Pam.
Lay chicken on bottom of pan.
Pour sour cream mixture over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with melted butter. Crumble over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf(very moist)
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 2 layer of extra strength tinfoil.
Place in large pan with 1 1/2 inches of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours; uncover last 15 minutes to brown.
You can stuff with your favorite stuffing.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cook cabbage, onions and bean sprouts in a little oil until soft.
Cook rice by directions.
Boil chicken and debone.
Mix all cooked ingredients well.
Get oil hot.
Put a tablespoon of mixture in middle of each wrapper and roll one side of wrapper over one time, then the two sides, then the other side.
Lay rolled side down on plate until you put it in the oil.
Cook until brown.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine mashed sweet potatoes with butter, orange juice, orange rind and salt. Form into balls and roll in cornflakes. Bake uncovered in butter baking dish at 350° about 45 minutes. Yield 12 servings.

title: chicken sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, chilies and chicken. Spread a little in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Put a little mixture in each tortilla and roll up. Do a full dozen like this. Top with onions and then the cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until the cheese is melted.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and cheese; add corn and chilies.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: indian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mrs. robinson's raisin cider sauce
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir in juice and raisins.
Over high heat, bring to a boil, stirring slowly and constantly until clear and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Serve over baked ham.

title: egg croquettes*
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and blend well.
Add milk and seasonings.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from fire, then add hard-cooked eggs.
Set in cool place, then shape into cakes. Roll in cracker crumbs, then in an egg and fry in hot fat.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into freezer and freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: toast by dave
directions: Plug in toaster.
Insert 2 slices of bread into toaster. Depress lever.
Toast 3 minutes.
Unplug toaster.
Insert knife into opening.
Pull out bread; scrape off burned part.
Spread on butter, 1/4-inch thick.
Enjoy!

title: pecan pie
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except pecans.
Then add pecans; mix well.
Pour mixture into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° for 35 to 40 minutes until you can insert knife in center and it comes out clean.

title: crunch-top potatoes
directions: Melt butter in jelly roll pan in 375° oven.
Add single layer of potatoes; turn once in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle over.
Bake 1/2 hour or until done.
Serves 4.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream Parkay until light and fluffy (I melt Parkay until soft). Sift together and stir in flour, powdered sugar and baking powder. Add pecans and vanilla.
Sift and set aside powdered sugar.

With fingers, shape into crescents and place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until delicately brown. Sprinkle powdered sugar on wax paper; put cookies on wax paper. Sift powdered sugar on top of warm cookies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together and bake in bread pans for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: icebox cake
directions: Prepare puddings as directed on packages.
Slice bananas.
In a large glass Pyrex pan (13 x 9-inches), layer pudding, crackers, bananas, etc.
Crush graham crackers and sprinkle on top. Refrigerate.
Serve with a dollop of Cool Whip.

title: almond crescents
directions: Put 2-3/4 c. almonds through your food grinder; *remaining 1/2 c. is for decorating and may be ground as well, but separately.
Beat egg whites until they hold a point, then add sugar, flour, vanilla and ground almonds.
Work dough with your hands until mixture holds together nicely.

title: zero fat snack(microwave)
directions: Put some pancake syrup and cinnamon on the cut apples.
Put into microwave for 2 minutes.
Let cool for about 5 minutes, then it's ready to eat.

title: egg custard
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup of hot water.
Dissolve sugar in it.
Put in refrigerator or freezer to almost set.
Then put the can of Carnation milk in your mixer and whip.
Slowly add the Jell-O mixture to the whipping cream.
Then add a few drops of yellow food coloring and lemon juice.

title: eagle brand strawberry pie
directions: Combine condensed milk and lemon juice.
Fold in nuts and strawberries, then fold in whipped topping.
Pour into pie shells. Chill and serve.

title: carrot salad
directions: Soak the raisins for a few minutes in water; drain.
Mix the mayonnaise with the cider vinegar and sugar.
Pour over carrots; toss well.

title: grandma's biscuits
directions: Grandma places her flour in a large bowl, makes a well in the center of it and adds the lard and milk to it.
Work it together and roll it out.
Cut out small biscuits.
Bake in 425° oven until golden brown.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the melted margarine, peanut butter, and confectioner's sugar. Shape into small balls, about 3/4 inch in diameter. In a double boiler over medium heat, melt the paraffin and the chocolate chips together. Dip the peanut butter balls into the melted chocolate. Drain on wax paper.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Arrange cabbage, onion and celery in layers.
Pour 1 cup sugar over top; do not stir.
Let stand while preparing dressing.
Bring to just a boil the vinegar, salt, mustard seed, celery seed and salt.
Pour over vegetable mixture; do not stir.
Cover tightly and let mixture set overnight.
Drain before serving.
Keeps 2 to 3 weeks.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening until crumbly. In a small bowl, combine eggs and milk; stir into crumb mixture just until moistened. Fold in blueberries. Pour the batter into two greased 9 inch round baking pans. Sprinkle with coconut. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Serve warm.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake in iron skillet at 350° until golden brown.

title: marvelous marinade(excellent for beef, chicken, fish.  great for game, too!)
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Place meat in a plastic bag (one gallon size) and pour in marinade.
Pour in one (12 ounce) bottle or can of beer. Mix gently.
Marinate meat for 2 hours to overnight (as you like).
Turn meat every few hours to ensure all sides of the meat are marinated.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef; salt and pepper to taste.
Drain fat.
Mix beef and pizza sauce and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer green peppers, onion, mushrooms and pepperoni over beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread sour cream over top.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over sour cream.
Cover with unrolled can of crescent rolls (rolls will be in a rectangle). Bake at 350° for an additional 20 minutes.

title: company beef casserole
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown beef in shortening.
Add onions, tomatoes, steak sauce, catsup, green pepper and parsley.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Combine spaghetti and beef mixture in large greased baking dish. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in the cream of mushroom soup. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, until bubbly and browned.
Serves 8.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix and drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: caramel apples
directions: You will also need 12 popsicle sticks.

title: chicken a greco
directions: Rub garlic cloves over chicken breasts.
Spray 9 x 11-inch cooking dish with Pam.
Place chicken in dish.
Add tomato paste mixed with 1 1/2 cups water.
Dash of salt, pepper and oregano. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring to boil the first 4 ingredients.
Boil 2 minutes.
Take off heat, add baking soda and stir well.
Put popped corn in a paper bag.
Pour caramel mixture over popped corn.
Fold bag and shake well.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes at full power.
Pour onto a cookie sheet to cool.

title: school house vegetable-beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain, rinse, and cool.
Add onion, garlic, and celery.
Cook briefly.	Add tomatoes and Veg-All with liquid.
Heat thoroughly, 20 to 30 minutes on low heat.
May add leftover vegetables (but no yucky ones). Freezes well.
Pretty good with buttered saltines crackers.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and Crisco.
Save 2/3 cup for 2 tops. To the remaining mixture, add baking powder, cinnamon, egg, soda and sour milk.
Beat briskly or use a mixer for 2 minutes, until batter is smooth.
Add 1/4 cup raisins to each and chopped nuts, if desired.
Pour into two 8-inch pans.
Scatter crumbs over tops and extra cinnamon.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: baked eggplant(mousaka)
directions: Add garlic, salt and pepper to ground beef.
Cook slowly until meat juices are absorbed.
Add chopped onion, parsley and butter; brown well.
Add tomato sauce, sugar and 1 cup water; simmer until thickened, about 15 minutes.
Slice eggplants; soak in deep bowl of salt water about 15 minutes.
Drain; squeeze slices gently to remove excess moisture.
Brush with vegetable oil; broil on both sides until browned.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, arrange layers of eggplant slices alternately with meat mixture, topping with eggplant.
Spread cream sauce over top; sprinkle with nutmeg or with grated cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: green and white salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, coarsely chop the broccoli and cauliflower.
Add celery, onions and pepper.
Mix together mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss to coat.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: lawrence's quick salad
directions: Add 3 cups water to 1 cup rice in covered casserole dish, place in oven at 350° until water is gone (approximately 10 minutes). Stir in salmon and juices until a paste.
Add celery and thoroughly mix.
Ideal salad or sandwich spread.

title: easy yokan
directions: Wash kanten; tear
into
pieces and soak in water.
Add sugar; bring to
a boil.
Add tsubushian; mix well.
Cook over low heat for
30 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
When cool, refrigerate.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour milk over bread and let soak for about 10 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and bake for about 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until top is golden brown.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; let cool.
In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise or salad dressing, shrimp, celery, peppers, onion and parsley.
Mix well.
Add macaroni; toss to coat.
Refrigerate 2 hours for flavors to blend.

title: scalloped potatoes with spinach and nutmeg
directions: Melt butter in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add onions and saute until translucent (about 8 minutes). Add spinach and cook until liquid evaporates, stirring occasionally, about 6 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
Cool.

title: iced box fruit cake
directions: Crumble crackers real fine. Add other ingredients together. Pour in milk and mix together real good until moist. Press firm into a round tube pan. Put in refrigerator and keep for 2 weeks before slicing.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain well.
Layer sausage, cereal, sausage and cereal.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Chill until mixture
begins to thicken.
Fold in remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: diabetic lemon pie
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water and mix well. Beat cream cheese with Cool Whip. Mix well. Add to Jell-O. Mix well. Line a pie plate with graham crackers broken into pieces. Pour in Jell-O mixture. Chill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder.
In a large bowl, combine bananas, sugar, butter, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add sifted ingredients.
Beat well.
Fold in nuts.
Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until bread tests for doneness.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: sweet and sour mustard
directions: In a medium bowl mix vinegar, both dry mustards and add honey and mayo.
Mix well.
Put into jars of your choice and refrigerate.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry onion and green pepper together with ground meat.
Mix beans, mustard, ketchup and brown sugar.
Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in deep dish.

title: congo squares
directions: Beat eggs, add brown sugar and shortening.
Mix well.
Sift in dry ingredients. Stir until well blended.
Add walnuts and chocolate bits.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits well.
Add water to juice to make 3 1/2 cups.
Add tapioca pudding.
Bring to a boil; pour over fruit (except bananas).
Cool, then add sliced bananas.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Take cauliflower, cut in pieces and cook in salt water, then drain.
Mix your soup, milk and cream cheese together; pour over cauliflower and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: surprise casserole
directions: Cook celery 10 minutes.
Drain.
Stir chicken soup and water chestnuts into cooked celery.
Pour into casserole dish.
Melt margarine.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix into margarine.
Add almonds.
Spread over celery mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: candied chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl except chicken. After mixing add chicken (smaller pieces work better).
Marinate in refrigerator for several hours.
Bake at 350° for about an hour or until done.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients.
Add and simmer 15 minutes the pizza sauce, tomato sauce, salt, garlic powder and oregano.
Cook noodles.
Divide in half the cheeses.
Put layer of half of the noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with half of the sauce and sprinkle half of the cheeses on top.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt gail's apple muffins
directions: Stir thoroughly first five ingredients.
(Make a well in the center.)
Blend egg, oil, milk and apples.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture on the top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
I love these.

title: mystery sandwich
directions: Put first 4 ingredients through food chopper.
Combine with mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.

title: imitation crab dip
directions: Mix the ingredients, adding the gelatine last.
Pour into a dish and refrigerate.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: In a medium bowl, mix butter, sugar and cocoa together; stir in eggs.
Add flour mixture, coconut and nuts; mix well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour dough into cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake for 30 minutes.
After removing from oven, spread Marshmallow Creme over cake.
When cool, frost or sprinkle chopped peanuts over Marshmallow Creme; serve with ice cream and fudge topping.

title: ritzy pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, add sugar and baking powder and vanilla by hand.
Add nuts and crackers.
Pour into greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Will be hard but cream softens it.
Spread with whipped cream when cool. Refrigerate overnight.

title: mom's best brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in a good-sized saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and mix (with a wooden spoon).
Add vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Add flour and salt (which have been sifted). Mix well nuts, if using.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cut in squares when completely cool.

title: gourmet carrots
directions: Combine in saucepan tomato soup, vinegar, mustard, salt, pepper, vegetable oil, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Stir until blended.
Pour over carrots, peppers and onions. Refrigerate overnight.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Melt butter and cocoa.
Add well beaten eggs and sifted flour and sugar, salt and nuts.
(Will be stiff.)
Pour into greased and floured pan (13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inches deep).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, depending on oven.
May add 1 cup chopped nuts to icing.
While hot, spread enough small marshmallows to cover top very well. Pour hot icing over top.
Let cool before serving.

title: chili peanuts
directions: To roasted peanuts, add chili powder and paprika.
Stir over very low heat until peanuts are hot.

title: sausage casserole
directions: In skillet, crumble and brown sausage, drain and cool.
Mix eggs, salt, and milk.
Stir in bread, cheese, and sausage.
Grease 9 x 13 baking dish.
Pour in mixture, cover, and refrigerate overnight.
Remove 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar while beating. Add eggs, one at a time.
Dredge chopped fruit and nuts in part of the sifted flour.
Add baking powder to the remaining flour and add to batter.
Add vanilla and lemon.
Fold in dredged fruit and nuts.
Pour batter into a tube pan which has been greased and lined with brown paper.
Start in a cold oven and bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: pumpernickel and spinach dip
directions: Squeeze all water from spinach.
Mix all ingredients together and serve in hollowed out round loaf of pumpernickel bread.
Serve with cubed bread from the center of loaf.
May also use rye bread.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Blend
all ingredients.
Heat until cheese melts.
Stir often. Makes 1 1/2 cups.	Serve with vegetables like potatoes and peas.

title: old-fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook to soft ball stage. Add peanuts and cook until mixture turns dark and will harden when a small amount is dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, baking soda and vinegar.
Stir well.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: meat loaf (blender)
directions: Tear bread in pieces.
Place milk, eggs, bread, onion, salt, oregano and pepper in blender.
Blend until combined.
In large mixing bowl, place ground beef and mixture and mix well.
Pat meat into loaf; place in pan and cover with catsup.
Add little water at sides of pan.
Bak eat 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peggy smith's cheesy lemon bars
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg; mix with fork until moist. Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased on bottom only.
Blend frosting into cream cheese.
Reserve 1/2 cup of cheese and frosting mixture.
Beat 3 to 5 minutes.
Spread over cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; spread with reserved frosting mixture.

title: double pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Flour and grease two cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together well.
Add vanilla.
Scald milk until it coats wooden spoon, stirring the entire time.
Add egg mixture to milk stirring continuously.
Pour egg-milk mixture into 1/4-quart baking dish and stir in raisins.
Cover top of custard heavily with nutmeg.
Place baking dish in a hot water bath and bake in moderately hot oven, 350°, for 1 hour.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Add onion and celery.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Gradually add dry ingredients, then stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple pie squares
directions: Mix in bowl, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Blend in Crisco. Break egg into measuring cup and beat well.
Add vinegar and water to make 3/4 cup.
Add to flour mixture, then knead. Roll half on wax paper to cover 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Save the other half for top.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter.
Pour in package of uncooked Creamettes.
Add salt, mustard, and grated cheese.
Pour milk over macaroni and cheese.
Do Not Stir.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, and at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and flour until thick.
Cool.
Slice a banana in the bottom of the crust.
Add cool mixture and sprinkle with nuts.
Top with Cool Whip.
Top with nuts and cherries to decorate.

title: pork chop dinners
directions: You will need 4 (16 x 12-inch) rectangular pieces of heavy-duty aluminum foil.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl using only 3/4 cup of the cream.
Make 40 small balls.
Coat with flour.
Brown in hot oil in skillet.
Drain on paper towel.
In same pan, melt butter. Stir in flour and blend.
Gradually stir in undiluted soup and 1/2 cup cream.
Bring to boil, stir; add meat and bay leaf.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Take out bay leaf.
Serve in chafing dish to keep hot.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and oleo.
Combine with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll into walnut-sized balls.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Press with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. (Real pretty if glass bottom has a pattern.)
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Put Hershey bars, marshmallows and milk in 2-quart bowl. Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes (stirring after 2 minutes) until melted.
Refrigerate for 30 to 40 minutes until chilled. Stir in 1 cup of Cool Whip to mixture.
Pour into pie crust and chill until set.
Before serving, top with remaining cup of Cool Whip.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir in milk, sugar, shortening, salt, egg and 2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in a greased 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until double in size.
Punch down and shape.

title: cucumber dip(satziki)
directions: To thicken yogurt, place 3 1/2 cups yogurt with 1 teaspoon salt in dish towel.
Hang over bowl until drippings stop, about 1 hour.
Sprinkle salt over cucumbers; let stand 15 minutes and press dry with paper towel.
Combine remaining ingredients and chill.
May be served with warm pita bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Put chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients.
Put in dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: jellied cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add cold water and chill until thickened.
Peel orange and cut segments in half.
Fold orange, drained pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts in gelatin.

title: apple crisp
directions: Line buttered 8-inch baking dish with apple slices.
Sift dry ingredients together; work in egg with pastry blender until consistency of coarse meal.
Sprinkle over apple slices.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Place oysters with liquid in medium saucepan. Combine flour, salt, Tabasco sauce and 2 tablespoons cold water.
Blend to a smooth paste and add to oysters. Simmer and stir over low heat about 5 minutes, just until edges of oysters begin to curl. Combine nonfat milk powder with remaining water.
Heat to scalding.
Do not allow to boil. Stir in oysters.
Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 15 minutes to blend flavors. Reheat stew to serving temperature.

title: german mushroom rice
directions: Saute bottoms of scallions or one good size onion.
Let get semi-soft.
Add mushrooms, then add rice and soy sauce.
Let cook ten minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Open cans of biscuits and cut each one into 4 pieces.
Roll each piece in sugar/cinnamon mixture until completely coated.
Put each piece in tube pan as finished.

title: almond fingers
directions: Tip:
You may add 1/2 cup coarsely ground almonds to cookie dough.
Reduce amount of flour to 2 1/4 cups.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour; add baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Sift together.
Add nuts and raisins; toss lightly to coat.
Measure sugar and add oil.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add pumpkin.
Add flour mixture and water, beating thoroughly until mixed.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Beat butter or margarine at low speed until smooth and creamy. Beat in sugar gradually until fluffy.
Mix in chocolate and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating 3 to 5 minutes after each addition.

title: tasty turnips
directions: Peel and dice turnips.
Boil with sugar, salt and pepper until tender.
Place in a colander to drain; rinse and set aside. Return turnips to pan.
Add melted butter to turnips and mash. Season to taste with more sugar, salt and pepper.
Butter is the secret to this recipe.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar and 2 cups of water in large freezer-safe container. Add orange juice and can of water. Stir until mixed well and orange juice is melted. Mix in pineapple, mandarin oranges and strawberries. Stir until strawberries are melted and everything is mixed well. Freeze for 1 to 2 hours. Stir and add in banana slices. Mix well. Return to freezer. Be sure to remove the salad about 1 hour before serving so it will be slushy when served.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; prepare 1 cup rice. Mix all ingredients together and place inside drained peppers.
Place in shallow pan and add 1 cup water in bottom of pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
(If you have any filling left over, place in small casserole and bake about 15 minutes.)

title: sesame chicken
directions: Put all ingredients in blender, except chicken.
Blend 1 minute.
Pour marinade over thawed chicken at least 30 minutes. Arrange in a single layer, skin side up, in baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Baste occasionally.

title: cherry nut fruit cake
directions: Cream well the margarine, gradually adding 1 1/2 cups of sugar.
Mix in cream cheese, eggs and vanilla.
Cream well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts and cherries. Use a spring-form pan; grease pan well.
Can use Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: poor man's shrimp
directions: In cold water, stir in salt until an egg in the shell will float.
Remove egg and add 1/4 cup more salt. Bring water to a boil.
Put salmon in water.
Return to boil.
Remove and serve hot with your favorite sauce.
Delicious.

title: individual steak dinner
directions: Wrap all ingredients in aluminum foil.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: bean dish
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add celery, onions, soup, tomato paste and ketchup. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Add all remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mello yello apple pie
directions: Roll out biscuits. Put apples on top and fold for fried pies. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Melt butter and drizzle over pies. Mix sugar and Mello Yello and pour over pie.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian ribs
directions: Cook all ingredients except ribs until clear and thick.
Pour over ribs in baking pan.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 350° oven. Cover until last 15 minutes.
Cut ribs into serving pieces.
(If country-style ribs are used, bake them a short time and pour out grease.)

title: double chip bars
directions: Place butter in a 13x9 pan; place in a 350 degree oven until melted. Remove from the oven. Sprinkle the cracker crumbs evenly over the butter. Press down. Pour milk evenly over crumbs. Sprinkle with chips; press down firmly. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on a wire rack before cutting.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix sugar, salt, black pepper, Miracle Whip and vinegar.
Add to vegetables and chill.

title: fried squash
directions: Boil squash and onion until very tender (about 30 minutes). Drain water.
Place into hot bacon grease.
Sprinkle sugar on top. Mix frequently until desired taste.

title: pitcher's oatmeal cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together first 6 ingredients.
Add shortening, egg and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in oats and nuts. Form into small balls.
Dip top in additional sugar.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Watch closely.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make in small balls.
Then flatten each ball.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Split sausages in half and brown.
Peel potatoes and slice round in 1/4-inch thick sections.
Mix all ingredients together and cook about 45 minutes to 1 hour on medium heat.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix well with a fork.
Roll between wax paper.
Makes a double crust.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Pour spaghetti sauce on meat and simmer on low heat for 1/2 hour.

title: jelly roll
directions: Sift flour with dry ingredients.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar gradually, beat well.
Add vanilla and flour gradually.
Turn into 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet with sides, lined with wax paper, greased or sprayed.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 13 minutes. Quickly roll in jelly roll on damp cloth or towel dusted with powdered sugar.
When cool, unroll and spread with jelly or any kind of filling and re-roll.
Slice and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend oil, vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix into apples.
Dough will be stiff.
Pat into greased 10 x 18-inch pan and sprinkle with nuts.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and buttermilk well.
Add well drained cocktail and mandarin oranges with some cookie pieces.
Put in bowl and put rest of cookie pieces on top.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients. Sift the next 3 ingredients. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Alternate with milk mixed with lemon juice. Add caraway seed and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
(Bake at 325° in a glass pan.)

title: pecan goodies
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Lightly grease large cookie sheet.
In medium-size bowl with electric mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in brown sugar until mixture is stiff and glossy.
Beat in vanilla extract; gently but thoroughly fold in pecans.
Drop mixture by heaping teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour, until outsides of candies are dry and set.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
If desired, dust candies lightly with mixture of cocoa powder and confectioners sugar.
Store in tightly covered containers in cool dry place up to 2 weeks.
Makes about 5 dozen candies.

title: glazed chicken
directions: In a shallow baking dish melt butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients except chicken.
Roll chicken in mixture, coating both sides.
Arrange chicken in dish, skin side up.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: lemon filling
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan; stir in water gradually.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add lemon peel and margarine.
Stir in lemon juice and food coloring; cool. If filling is too soft, refrigerate until set.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: After slicing eggplant, put in a last bowl of salted cold water for 15 minutes; then drain.

title: yogurt dip
directions: Peel cucumber and remove seed; grate and drain.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill for several hours before serving. Serve with chips or assorted raw vegetables.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: spanish rice dish
directions: Mix together rice, onion, tomatoes, oil, green pepper and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, covered.
Stir occasionally.
Mix in chicken and shrimp and heat.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add 1 cup sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift in dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites.
Add 1/3 cup sugar gradually, until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Add 1 cup nuts.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) pans and bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
Top with your favorite frosting and on sides and between layers.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: gazpacho
directions: Crush garlic in salt (salt can be optional).
Saute mushrooms in olive oil.
Add garlic and mushrooms to remaining ingredients and let stand in glass or stainless steel container at least 3 hours (preferably overnight).
Serve with garlic croutons.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion in skillet.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and water to meat.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: successful meringue
directions: In saucepan, moisten cornstarch in a small amount of water. Stir in the boiling water.
Cook until thick and clear.
Cool.
In bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Add salt and then add sugar gradually.
Beat in the cooked and cooled cornstarch and beat until of the right consistency to stand in pretty peaks.
Top pie and brown as usual in a 375° oven.

title: creamed escarole and cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower in 1-inch boiling water with 1/2 teaspoon salt in large skillet for 10 minutes or until cauliflower is crisp-tender.
Drain; set aside.
Melt butter in skillet (I used bacon and drained it).
Add escarole; cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour; mix well.
Stir in milk and cream; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and comes to a boil.
Stir in Swiss cheese, remaining 3/4 teaspoon salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Add cooked cauliflower; heat through and serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: nancy's ham-broccoli rolls
directions: Roll one slice of ham and one slice of cheese around one cooked broccoli spear.
Heat oven to 350°.
Combine soup, sour cream and mustard in saucepan and heat (do not boil).
Place ham rolls in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and pour sauce over top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hot wings
directions: Cut wings into two pieces, discarding wing tips.
Cook on rack over pan in oven at 425° for one hour.
Turn after half hour.
Melt butter or margarine and add hot sauce.
Pour over cooked wings and marinate at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Place on rack again and broil for 5 minutes on each side, until crisp.

title: green pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and place in crock-pot with 2 cups salt and water to cover.
Let set for 3 days.
Next 3 days drain and cover with fresh water.
On the 7th day, simmer for 1 1/2 hours with 3 quarts of water, 1 cup white vinegar and alum.
Drain.
Add syrup.

title: angel surprise dessert
directions: In a small mixer bowl, gradually blend milk into cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Add pudding mix and beat at low speed of electric mixer until smooth and slightly thickened, about 2 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine(egg, bacon and cheese pie)
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pie shell.
Beat eggs slightly, beat in remaining ingredients. Pour mixture into pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300 degrees and bake 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 meal size servings or 8 appetizer size servings.
Left overs can be reheated in microwave.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix and chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: miracle lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: skillet beef pilaf
directions: In a deep 9 or 10-inch skillet, saute the onion and green pepper in oil until tender. Add beef and cook, breaking up with a spoon, until the meat loses red color. Season with salt and pepper. Add rice. Cook and stir until rice looks translucent, but not brown (3 to 4 minutes). Add 1/2 cup broth. Cook and stir until broth is absorbed.
Add remaining 2 cups broth. Cover and simmer until rice is tender and liquid absorbed, about 20 minutes. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: egg salad sandwiches
directions: Mash eggs together. Add sweet relish and mayonnaise. Mix well.

title: creamy chicken with asparagus
directions: Melt butter over low heat in saucepan; stir in flour, onion and seasoned salt until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in milk.
Return to heat to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and 1/2 cup cheese; heat just until cheese is melted and chicken is hot.
Serve creamed chicken over asparagus spears; top with remaining cheese.

title: honeyed chicken
directions: Place chicken in roasting dish, side by side, and salt generously. Cover the meat with all the vegetables and salt them well. Melt honey and butter over low heat. Stir well and pour this over the meat and vegetables. Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until meat and vegetables are done.

title: baked orange chicken
directions: Brown chicken pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine orange juice, orange rind, paprika, mustard, margarine and ginger root.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake for one hour.
Turn after 30 minutes.
Serve with rice and peas.

title: raisin-bran muffins
directions: Blend ingredients just until moist.
Add 1 1/2 cups walnuts. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake in 400° preheated oven 20 minutes.
Mixture keeps in refrigerator several weeks.

title: spiced chicken wings
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Shake in hot sauce and some garlic powder. Dip wings in sauce and lay on tray. Sprinkle dry dressing on wings.
Cook for 1 hour at 425° or until brown. Serve with garlic bread.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: children's summer sandwiches
directions: Slice ingredients.
Put everything on a plate and let the kids make their own combination sandwiches.

title: kentucky green beans
directions: String and break beans.
Put in a large pot.
Add salt pork, bacon grease and salt.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over medium heat.
Cook for approximately 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add water, as necessary.
Let water cook down for the last 45 minutes.

title: cheese cake(crostata)
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Drain Ricotta cheese and beat until smooth.
Slowly
add
cups sugar and egg yolks, beating after
each
addition.
Beat in flour, lemon rind and lemon extract.
Beat
egg
whites
with remaining sugar until stiff. Blend
with
whipped
cream and fold in Ricotta cheese mixture. Butter
heavily a 12-inch spring-form pan and sprinkle
with graham
cracker crumbs.
Pour filling into prepared pan
and
bake for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake
hour. Turn off heat and allow to cool in oven.
Keep refrigerated.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates.
Add margarine.
Let stand 10 minutes in a large bowl.
Add and stir in by hand all at once the remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 loaf.
Serve with cream cheese.

title: water chestnut appetizers
directions: Soak water chestnuts in teriyaki sauce overnight.
Cut bacon strips in half.
Roll each water chestnut in a piece of uncooked bacon and stick a toothpick through it to hold the bacon on.
Place these on a cookie sheet covered in foil and bake until desired crispness.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Combine peeled and sliced apples with NutraSweet and flour. Make crust for 2 crust pie and fill.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: hungarian frosting
directions: Combine chocolate, sugar and water.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add butter, one tablespoon at a time, beating until spreading consistency.
Fills and frosts top and sides of two 9-inch layers.
I use Pillsbury or Betty Crocker Dutch chocolate frosting in can now adays.

title: tortellini and beef soup
directions: Cut the carrots into 1/4-inch slices and set aside.
Coarsely chop the onion.
In
a medium saucepan, warm the oil over medium-high heat until hot.
Add the onion and garlic and stir-fry until the mixture begins to brown, about 3 minutes.
Crumble in the beef and cook, stirring, until the meat is no longer pink, about 3 minutes.
Add the beef broth, water and crushed tomatoes. Cover and bring the mixture to a boil over medium-high heat.
Add the carrots, basil and pepper and cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, for about 2 minutes.
Add the tortellini and cook until al dente, 10 to 12 minutes or according to package directions.

title: banana nog
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Whip for 30 seconds. Pour into 2 chilled glasses.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients, mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: friendship bread
directions: For starter, combine 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup milk.

title: southern style chicken stew
directions: Dredge chicken in flour.
Cook a few pieces at a time in large, heavy skillet.
Remove pieces as they brown.
To drippings, add onions and cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Blend in curry powder and cook 1 minute longer.
Return chicken to pot and add broth, tomatoes, carrots, apples, salt and pepper.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 20-25 minutes, until fork tender.
Skim off fat.
Add green beans and cook 10 minutes linger.
Add corn and heat through.
Serves 4-6.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Be sure water covers cucumbers. Let set 24 hours. Rinse real good, then cover with alum water (2 gallons water to 1 box alum). Let set 24 hours. Rinse slightly and drain. Make syrup (2 quarts white vinegar, 9 cups sugar, 2 tablespoons pickling spices tied in bag and boiled with pickles). Use 1 teaspoon turmeric. Heat; pour over cucumbers. Let set 24 hours, then bring all to boil. Cook for 5 minutes, then can.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix liquid ingredients together.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and soda together and add to liquid mixture.
Mix to a smooth batter. Add cereal and nuts.
Mix it all together.
Refrigerate overnight. Batter makes four dozen muffins.
Use muffin tins with cupcake liners.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until they are set up on top.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon in hot fat and brown.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and cinnamon sifted together alternately with pineapple.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: roxie(appetizer)
directions: Melt cheese and butter in microwave.
Add everything else. Spread on English muffins (mixture runny).
Freeze for 1 hour only.
Take out. Cut into 8 pieces.
Put back in freezer in baggies.
Bake frozen at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: coke chicken
directions: Mix ketchup, Coke and worcestershire sauce.
Spread over fryer pieces.
Cook in covered skillet at 200 degrees, turning occasionally until done.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Mix together and heat.
Serve with tortilla chips or Fritos.

title: marinated chicken kabobs
directions: Stir dressing mix, orange juice and vegetable oil in large bowl.
Add chicken and vegetables; toss to coat.
Cover. Refrigerate 3 hours.
Arrange chicken and vegetables on skewers. Broil 3 inches from heat 16 minutes or until cooked through turning frequently.
(We cook them on grill in Summer time.)

title: beef marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Marinate beef 1 hour or longer.
Grill to desired doneness.

title: capital cake
directions: From Jane's Grandmother's cookbook.
Very old.
No date can be found.
This recipe was from the "House Keeping in Old Virginia". The cake was to be baked in a wood stove until done (350°).

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Pour over hot base and bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: orange-butter coffee cake
directions: In bowl, soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water (110° to 115°). Stir in eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, sour cream, 6 tablespoons butter and salt.
Stir in 2 3/4 cups flour.
On floured surface, knead in enough flour to make a moderately soft dough that is smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl; turn once.
Cover and let rise until double (1 1/2 hours).
Punch down.

title: peanut butter marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to soft ball stage.
Take off fire; add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat and pour into buttered pan.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil one chicken with one teaspoon salt.
Debone chicken and put into broth.
Mix flour, eggs and water.
Shape mixture into ball and roll on floured board until thin; cut into strips and put in boiling broth.

title: chili and enchiladas
directions: Chop onion, reserving half for filling.
Cook beef and remaining onion in a large skillet over medium-high heat, 5 to 6 minutes, stirring until beef crumbles and is no longer pink; drain and return to skillet.

title: busy day pickles
directions: First Day:
Pack washed cucumber slices into a large, plastic or glass jar.
Add alum and cover with water.

title: tiramisu
directions: Tiramisu, which in Venetian dialect means "pick me up", is a very old dessert that was first concocted in or around Venice toward the end of the 1700's.
Legend has it that it was formulated for Casanova and other rakes, craving the energy generated by its high content of caffeine and sugar.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Cook 1 cup of fresh blueberries, sugar, water and cornstarch together until mixture begins to thicken and turns blue.
Into cooled pie shell, put remaining 3 cups uncooked blueberries.
Pour cooked mixture on top.
Refrigerate; top with Cool Whip.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple chunks.
Save juice.
In double boiler, mix pineapple juice, sugar, butter and cornstarch.
Mix fruit.
Pour paste over fruit after paste has cooled.

title: egg nog candy
directions: Combine egg nog, sugar, corn syrup and salt in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Cook until syrup reaches 235° on candy thermometer or until it forms soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Stir frequently to prevent scorching.
Cool sugar mixture to lukewarm and add butter, beating constantly until candy begins to lose its gloss.
Stir in cherries and nuts and spread into buttered pie plate.
Do this quickly or candy will set in saucepan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well. Sift soda and flour.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Add flavoring and food coloring.
Bake in 3 layers at 350°.

title: imperial crab
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add onion and mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: corned beef
directions: Place brisket into roasting pan or Dutch oven or crock-pot, add water, garlic, bay leaves and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions; cook covered 10 minutes.
Add cabbage, cook, covered 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaves. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Make a hole in flour mixture and into it put eggs (unbeaten), sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Add soda to buttermilk and add them and nutmeg to first mixture.
Mix and roll out; cut with a doughnut cutter or form into desired shape.
Fry in a heavy aluminum skillet, turning once until they are brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Stir milk and oil into egg. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Stir in berries. Stir into 12 muffin-lined cups. Top with Crumb Topping. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit tea(serves 15)
directions: In medium saucepan, combine water, sugar, cloves and cinnamon. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Cover and steep 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and strain; cool slightly.
In a large pitcher, combine fruit juices and tea.
Chill and serve over ice or heat and serve in mugs.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and bananas.
Add nuts, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt mixture.
Beat well.
Pour in greased loaf pan and bake at 325° until done, about 1 hour.

title: vegetable beef stew
directions: Place beef in a large pot with 2 1/2 quarts water. Add 1 tablespoon salt, pepper and 1 chopped onion.
Combine bay leaves, oregano and thyme; tie in a cheesecloth bag and drop into pot with meat.
Cover and simmer 3 hours.
Cut meat into bite size pieces and add to stock.
Add potato chunks, cabbage, 1 chopped onion and 1 tablespoon salt.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add 2 cups water, tomatoes, sugar, frozen veggies and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook for 1 hour longer.
Yields 6 quarts.

title: quick mix pumpkin dessert
directions: Beat together the first six ingredients slowly until blended. Chill 5 minutes, then fold in Cool Whip and miniature marshmallows.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and top with nuts. Chill overnight or for several hours.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Push about 1/4 cup cream through the baked casserole; let set 10 minutes, then serve.)

title: cranberry pudding
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add flour and melted butter or margarine.
Add almond extract and beat well.
Pour over berries.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over batter before baking. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; add remaining ingredients.
Put in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Spread filling in 8-inch square buttered pan.
Put dry cake cake on top.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: maple eggnog
directions: In large pitcher, combine ingredients.
Chill.
Stir before serving.
Garnish with whipped cream and nutmeg, if desired. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 1 quart.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Beat eggs; combine them in a saucepan with the sugar, flour and juice from the pineapple.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, stir into the fruit-marshmallow-cheese mixture.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: eveready biscuits
directions: Note:
This recipe divides very nicely to make half of it.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Saute celery and onion in butter until clear.
Add to first 4 ingredients and toss well.
Add eggs and water.
Stuff turkey or chicken or bake in greased, covered casserole dish for approximately 1 hour.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix the dry ingredients well.
Add eggs, water and oil.
Mix well.
Add bananas and mix.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake about 55 minutes in 325° oven.
Let cool in pan. Turn out and glaze with mixture of 1/2 banana (mashed), 1 tablespoon lemon juice and 2 cups powdered sugar.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: A cast-iron skillet works the best!

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Coat pieces of chicken heavily with crumb mixture.
Bake in shallow pan, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt shortening.
Remove from heat; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, then chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch, well greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown hamburger
in
a	large skillet; drain off excess fat. Stir
in
the
chopped
onion; continue cooking over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add chopped green pepper, sliced olives, stewed tomatoes,
tomato sauce, drained corn and chili powder. Simmer over low
heat
for
minutes.
Place
in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir in 3/4 of the crushed corn chips and 3/4 of the
grated
cheese.
Sprinkle the remaining chips and cheese over the
top.
Bake,
uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crawfish fettuccine(from lee bailey's new orleans)
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil while you prepare the sauce.
In a large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter and saute peppers and yellow onion over high heat, stirring, 2 or 3 minutes, until well-wilted.
Add crawfish tails, Creole seasoning, pepper flakes and salt.
Reduce heat and cook 2 to 3 minutes.

title: nut rolls
directions: Cream butter (not oleo).
Heat milk; add yeast.
Pour over butter and sugar.
Add flour enough to make dough firm.
Place in refrigerator overnight or 1/2 day.
Roll out thin; spread with walnuts and brown sugar to which enough water is added to moisten. Spread filling.
Cut in rectangles; roll in crescent shape.
Roll in sugar and bake until nice and brown.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions, green peppers and garlic in oil.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add tomatoes and cook until thick stirring constantly.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Heat through. Shrimp should simmer 3 to 5 minutes to be done.
Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch pieces; dredge in flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Heat skillet with the oil; lightly brown on all sides. Transfer meat to a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Lightly brown onions and celery in oil; add to the meat.
Heat soup and water; add to meat mixture.
Add bay leaf and cloves; stir well.
Add potatoes and carrots; stir well.
Cover casserole and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Take out the bay leaf before serving.
Serves 4.

title: oatmeal raisin bars
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, stir together first 4 ingredients. Stirring occasionally, bring to boil over medium heat. Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended. Press evenly into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are lightly brown. Cut into squares. Store in	tightly covered container.

title: ginger peachy ice cream sandwiches
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and spices.
Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat egg.
Combine 2 tablespoons of the egg with the molasses and beat into butter mixture.
(Save remaining egg for another use.)
Stir in flour mixture.
Divide dough into 2 pieces; chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll out 1 piece of dough at a time between sheets of floured waxed paper to about 1/8-inch thick.
With a 3-inch cutter, stamp out cookies. Dust off excess flour.
Put about 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake until edges begin to brown, about 10 minutes.
Cool. Put about 1/2 cup ice cream on 8 of the cookies.
Top each with another cookie.
Press down slightly and smooth edges.
Freeze. Makes 8 Sandwiches.

title: foolproof flaky pie crust
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
To this mixture, add Crisco and work together.
Add vinegar to ice water.
Then add to previous mixture.
Roll.
Makes 3 medium pie crusts or whatever, depending on the thickness of the crusts you roll.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order listed.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
A golden brown crust will form on top.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet.
Mix all ingredients together.
Top with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Combine beans, mustard, onion, barbecue sauce and rest of ingredients; top with bacon.
Cover and cook with microwave energy 10 minutes.

title: make ahead oriental salad
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl; toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour over vegetables; stir gently.
Cover and chill overnight.
Use slotted spoon to serve. Keeps well in refrigerator until used.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix stuffing with butter.
Spread half of mixture in a 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Cook squash and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix soup, sour cream, carrots and cooked squash.
Toss lightly to combine.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until top is brown and bubbly.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients in an electric mixer for 10 minutes. In separate bowl, cut apples up in fine pieces.
Add cinnamon, sugar and nuts.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Arrange in layers, first batter, then apples.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter until done.
Add beans and cook 10 minutes.
Mix last 4 ingredients and add to other mixture. Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, for 45 minutes.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Cream together the margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Mix together the milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Mix these two mixtures together.

title: taffy lollypops
directions: Combine and bring to boil.
Turn to medium heat.
Boil to hard ball on candy thermometer.
Add vanilla.
Pour into buttered muffin pans and place lollypop or popcycle stick in each.

title: 100 good cookies
directions: Blend sugars with butter until creamy.
Add egg, oil and next 5 ingredients and blend well.
Add final 4 ingredients and mix. Roll into small balls, press with fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes in oven preheated to 350°.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 4 tablespoons warm water. Sift dry ingredients together. Add remaining ingredients, stirring well. Roll out on floured surface. Cut out biscuits.
Bake at 400° until brown in ungreased pan. Dough may be stored in refrigerator for several days.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour brown sugar over butter.
Add drained pineapple.
Mix cake mix using pineapple juice plus enough water to equal amount called for by mix.
(Optional:
Can use rum to equal liquid instead of water.) Bake as directed.
Turn cake out of pan when done.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Lightly spray oven-to-table dish or Pyrex pie plate with Pam.
Add mixture and bake at 325° to 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot with snack rye crackers, bagel, pita chips, endive or veggies.

title: hawaiian grilled pork chops
directions: Drain pineapple juice, saving 1/4 cup juice; set aside.
Place chops in a large, shallow dish.
Combine pineapple juice and next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over chops.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.
Remove chops, saving marinade.
Grill over medium coals 40 to 45 minutes, turning frequently and basting with marinade during last few minutes of cooking time.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Add one teaspoon sugar; set aside.
Place shortening and remaining sugar in large mixing bowl. Add 2 cups boiling water, mix and cool to lukewarm.
Beat in eggs and yeast.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and put a plate on top.
Place in refrigerator.
After 2 hours, punch bowl; let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: italian style sausage-bean soup
directions: Drain beans, then put in a saucepan; cover with water.
Boil for 10-15 minutes.
Brown sausage; drain off fat.
Add to slow cooker with beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low 8 - 12 hours.
Serve with Parmesan cheese and Italian bread.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: *Tip:
Thin slices cut from a 5-ounce or 6-ounce package of Hormel pepperoni can be used.

title: herbed biscuits
directions: Pour melted butter into 8-inch round cake pan.
Sprinkle onion, dill and poppy seed over butter.
Place cheese in large Ziploc bag.
Cut biscuits into 4 pieces.
Add biscuits to bag and shake.
Arrange biscuits in pan and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 14 to 16 minutes or until golden brown. Serve immediately.

title: french toast
directions: In bowl, mix eggs and milk.
Beat until well blended.
Add 1/4 teaspoon vanilla and 1 tablespoon cinnamon sugar.
Sprinkle in nutmeg.
Dunk bread in mixture and fry until golden brown.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; add garlic, salt, tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles in large amount of boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella.
Layer half of the noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread half the Ricotta filling.
Add half of the Mozzarella cheese, then half the meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
(Or assemble early and refrigerate; bake 45 minutes.)
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: oyster cracker tidbits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir in crackers.
Pour oil over cracker mixture; stir from bottom.
Seal in airtight container.
These will stay fresh for several weeks.
Makes 6 cups.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour with soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt. Cream shortening; add sugar and molasses.
Blend well and add egg. Then add dry ingredients.
Form into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Press a raisin in center of each cookie before baking.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 24 to 30 cookies.

title: tomato chili sauce
directions: Put tomatoes in boiling water to remove skins.
Put skinned tomatoes back in pan and squish them until they are in pieces. Add salt (to taste) and the rest of ingredients.
Simmer until thick.
Store in Mason jars.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, with electric mixer at low, cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Add flour mixture; beat until blended.
Stir in coconut, chocolate and pecans.
Drop by teaspoons
2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove cookies to wire racks to cool.
Store cookies in lightly covered container.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an 11 x 15-inch well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: wormy apples(a creepy crawly treat!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scoop out the centers of the apples. Place apples on a cookie sheet.
Fill the holes with red hots candy.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with gummy worms.

title: party snack
directions: Mix.
Pour mixture over 2 (12 ounce) packages of oyster crackers.
Let set for 1 hour.

title: nona's rice cheese pie
directions: Scald milk and stir in rice.
Add salt to taste and let cook until tender but firm and milk is absorbed.
Let cool.
Turn Ricotta into a bowl.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add raisins (optional) and flavoring and blend well.
Fold in cooked rice.

title: chunky macadamia nut white chocolate cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with electric mixer until it is fluffy; gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add egg and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in morsels and nuts; drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool on wire racks.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: hummus bi-tahini(lebanese side dish and dip)
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in a blender, adding drained bean liquid to come just below the level of the beans.
Puree to an almost smooth, thick paste.
If a thinner consistency is desired, add more liquid.
Taste for seasoning and correct, if necessary. Place in a shallow platter and cover with 2 tablespoons olive oil. Garnish with whole beans and parsley.

title: 7 cup salad
directions: Fold together and chill for 1 hour.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Good on lettuce wedges or tossed salad.

title: cubed pork casserole
directions: Brown meat, celery, onion and green pepper.
Mix all together with other ingredients.
Bake 2 hours at 350°, uncovered, in a 2-quart casserole.

title: raw potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes.
Beat egg yolks; stir in potatoes and flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg whites until rounded peaks are formed.
Fold into the potato mixture.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons of batter in a hot greased skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: instant russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in jars.
As needed, use 2 heaping teaspoons per cup of hot water.
If you do not use dehydrated lemon rind, you may add a dash of lemon juice or slice of lemon when you add hot water.

title: jewish cheese pie
directions: Bake at 475° for 10 minutes. Serve cold.

title: delicious stuff
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Mix jello with water.
Allow to cool. Afterwards, combine all other ingredients with pudding and jello. Put in long Pyrex dish to chill.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate chicken wings at joints and dispose of wing tips.
Bake wings on greased aluminum foil covered baking sheets for approximately 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix sauce ingredients.
Baste with sauce every 10 minutes for another 50 minutes.
Serve with extra napkins.

title: broiled red snapper
directions: Mix lemon juice and seasonings.
Brush onto fish; let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Next, brush the fish with margarine. Spray rack on baking pan with Pam.
Place fish on rack and put the pan in a preheated oven.
Broil uncovered for 10 minutes on each side or until done.
Serve hot.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Place in serving dish, cover with chili sauce and sprinkle with crabmeat.
Chill.
Serve over Ritz crackers.

title: rich and charlie's 'chicken modiga'
directions: Melt 1/4 cup of margarine in saucepan and set aside.
Cut remaining 1/2 cup of margarine/butter in half.
Put margarine and flour in mixing bowl.
Mash with fork to make creamy mixture.
Set aside.

title: kufta
directions: Peel potatoes and slice into thin rounds (like for potato chips).
Parboil; drain and set aside.
Combine beef, spices, onion and finely cut parsley or cilantro.
Shape into hamburger patties or 4 to 6-inch sausage rolls.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook the squash with onion.
Drain and mix with other ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 or 45 minutes.

title: marinated carrot pennies
directions: Put carrots, onions, green peppers into casserole dish.
Bring the remaining ingredients to a boil and pour over the carrot, onion, green pepper mixture.

title: simple lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat; add sauce and simmer.
Boil noodles; layer hamburger mixture, noodles and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: no-crust egg custard
directions: In a large Pyrex dish, rub margarine in dish.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chee chee(pina colada)
directions: Mix and freeze.
Scoop in glass and add 7-Up or Squirt.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Mix ingredients with electric mixer.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet; bake in a 350° oven until browned, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Can freeze and reheat 15 minutes at 350°.

title: four large pumpkin pies
directions: Mix all together except save out egg whites and beat stiffly; fold in last.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and peanut butter; mix well. Gradually add sugar; cream after each addition.
Add eggs and milk, mixing well.
Sift together flour and soda.
Blend with first mixture.
Drop teaspoonful of dough onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add salt and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead well.
Let stand 1/2 hour, covered.
Roll out very thin.
Spread on cloth to dry.
Must not be sticky or so dry it will be brittle.
Cut into 3-inch strips.
Layer them, cut crosswise in very fine strips and toss them lightly to separate. Spread out to dry.
Put into covered jar for future use.
Drop into boiling soup 5 minutes before serving.

title: favorite lemon cutout cookies
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine all cookie ingredients.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed, 1 to 2 minutes. If desired, divide dough and color with food coloring (mix in well).
Wrap dough in waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until firm, 2 to 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll out dough, 1/3 at a time, on a well-floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut out with cookie cutters (hearts for Valentine's Day, animal shapes for any day, Christmas shapes, etc.).
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
If desired, sprinkle colored sugars over tops or bake and decorate later with frosting.
Bake for 6 to 10 minutes, or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove immediately; cool completely.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Melt butter in small pan and add rolled oats; stir until all oats are coated with butter.
Beat egg until foamy.
Add sugar and beat until light.
Add baking powder and flour to egg mixture, then mix in oatmeal and butter mixture.
Stir in orange rind. Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Drop batter, 1/2 tablespoon at a time, about 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° until golden (about 8 to 12 minutes), watching carefully.
Allow to cool about 1 minute, then remove.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: yankee chile
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Add other ingredients to meat in a large pot, heat and serve.

title: jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan.
Add green pepper, celery, onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is soft and translucent.
Add broth, tomatoes and spices.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes. Add chicken, shrimp, rice and sausage slices.
Cook until shrimp are pink.

title: beef hash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes.

title: skillet vegetables
directions: Lay 3 slices of bacon in the bottom of the skillet.
Layer carrots, potatoes and cabbage over the bacon.
Sprinkle with salt (optional).
Add 1 cup of water.
Cover and steam over slow heat for about 25 minutes.

title: mushrooms and rice
directions: Saute onions (sliced and separated) in butter in frying pan. Cook until they begin to turn clear.
