Add drained mushrooms; cook until brown.
Add rice; stir until all rice is coated.
Pour consomme over mixture in pregreased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: sunday punch
directions: Chill juices and ginger ale. Make ice ring of apple juice and cherries or orange slices. Can do ahead. Serves 40.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Mix ingredients well with fingers.
Put rack or some leaves in bottom of heavy pan.
Use a couple of teaspoons on inside of leaf and roll neatly.
Place open end on bottom and repeat until all stuffing is used.
Be sure to tuck sides of leaf in as you roll and crisscross layers so leaves don't open.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Grate onion in mixing bowl, then add remaining ingredients. The longer you beat the whole mixture, the better it will stay together.
Use blender.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Put filling in pie crust.

title: cheese-meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Shape in a loaf in a baking pan. Bake at 350° (moderate oven) about 1 hour until browned.
Yields 6 servings.

title: caramel-nut pudding cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put into an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine the ground beef, corn flake crumbs, parsley flakes, eggs, soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder and onion.
Form meat balls and place in 9 x 15-inch pan.
In a saucepan, put the cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice; heat until the cranberry sauce is melted.
Pour the sauce over the meatballs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, margarine and butter.
Beat in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour, then vanilla. Add chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: angel cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into small balls.
Bake in a 350° oven for 18 to 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Arrange deboned
chicken
in
an
8 x 4 x 2-inch baking dish. Drizzle
butter over chicken.
Place cooked and drained broccoli around
chicken.
Blend
soup, milk and cheese; pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with chips.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes until heated through.

title: easy strawberry cheese cake
directions: Mix soft cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Place strawberries on top.
Chill and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Layer green beans and Shoepeg corn in buttered casserole dish. Saute onions in butter.
Add sour cream and cream of celery soup. Bring all to a boil.
Pour ingredients into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with 1 stick melted butter.
Pour over casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix first six ingredients together and put into buttered square baking dish.
Mix rest of ingredients together to make topping and spread over apples.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: chinese oven dish
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in casserole dish for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Boil brown sugar, Karo and butter until it forms a soft ball. Remove from heat and add cream and vanilla.
Will keep in the refrigerator for some time.

title: bubble and squeak
directions: In a skillet, heat fat.
Fry onion in fat until softened. Remove onion with slotted spoon.

Mix onion and cooked cabbage or other vegetables into mashed potatoes, along with salt and pepper. Spoon mixture into frying pan and flatten to make large, flat cake. Fry gently over medium heat, 15 minutes on first side.
Turn it over and cook a few minutes to brown other side.
Cut into wedges and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
In saucepan, mix remaining ingredients and simmer.
Combine with ground beef.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Mix and let stand 30 minutes.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thick and cut out.
Fry in deep fat until brown; serve with honey.

title: everyone's favorite hot dish
directions: Mix stuffing as box directs.
Put in an 11 x 7-inch casserole.
Add vegetables, cooked as package directs.
Blend chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix together kraut, celery, green pepper and onion.
Cover with vinegar, oil and sugar.
Let stand overnight.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients just enough to blend.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan and bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: pickled pears
directions: Make a syrup with the sugar, vinegar and cinnamon.
Cook them together for 20 minutes.
Cook pears in syrup until tender, a few at a time.
Put pears in jar; boil the syrup 10 minutes longer, then pour over pears and seal.

title: john's chili recipe
directions: Brown chopped onions in vegetable oil.
Add water, ground beef, chili powder, red pepper and salt to onion mixture.
Cook until ground beef is done, approximately 45 minutes.
Add ketchup. Simmer for 30 minutes longer.

title: autumn pudding
directions: Mix all of the casserole ingredients together and place in 2 1/2-quart dish.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix in a large bowl the flour and sugar.
Mix in a small pan the Crisco oil, Coca-Cola and cocoa.
Bring this to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Then add buttermilk, soda, vanilla, eggs and marshmallows.
Mix all together and pour into greased 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 40 minutes at 325°.

title: coke float
directions: Get a cup and poor Coke in it.
Get a spoon and ice cream, put in the cup.

title: sherried pecans
directions: Heat pecans in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes at 325°.
Stir often.
Heat the sherry, margarine, sugar, nutmeg and salt.
Pour over pecans and bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Stir often (every 5 minutes).
Pour out on foil.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Combine bran, sugar and sifted flour with soda and salt in large bowl.
Add mixture of eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Mix well. Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep 6 weeks.
Fill muffin tins or paper liners 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: easy apple crunch
directions: Place apples in 9 x 10-inch glass pan. Sprinkle cake mix evenly over apples. Drizzle butter over cake mix and add nuts on the top. Bake at 350° in a preheated oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Top with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream. Good hot or cold.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Using a punch bowl, start with Cool Whip, then cake (broken in pieces).
Line bottom of bowl.
Divide ingredients and layer them 2 times.
End with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Decorate with cherries or strawberries on top.
Serves a large group. Enjoy.

title: large chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone and place in an 11 x 14-inch baking dish.
Scatter onion and vegetables over chicken.
Mix Bisquick mix and milk together.
Pour this over the chicken, onion, vegetables and soup mixture.
(Do not stir.)
Drop pats of margarine over top of all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chocolate-orange muffins
directions: In medium bowl, beat together 1 cup sugar and oil.
Stir in juice and eggs.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Blend into sugar-egg mixture just until mixed.
Stir in orange slices and chocolate chips just until mixed.

title: harvest soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pot.
Cook until cabbage is done.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Can be frozen.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes (put through blender or cut with edge of spoon), paste, water, parsley, salt, garlic powder, pepper, oregano and allspice.
Simmer uncovered about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook lasagna as directed and drain.

title: hot dogs in sauce
directions: Cut hot dogs in half diagonally.
Mix mustard and preserves and heat thoroughly until preserves are melted.
Heat hot dogs but do not cook through.
Combine hot dogs with sauce mixture.
Serve in fondue pot or crock pot.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together butter, shortening, eggs, sugar and salt.
Add soda and flour.
Mix together well.
Take about 1 tablespoon of dough.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in sugar and cinnamon.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and bake in 2 (9-inch) cake pans or 3 (8-inch) cake pans according to package instructions.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt, soda and baking powder and blend.
Alternate sour cream and flour until all has been added; blend well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: milk chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add melted candy bars.
Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to chocolate mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.

Add pecans, chocolate syrup and vanilla, blending well. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.
Sift a small amount of powdered sugar over cake, if desired.
Yields a 10-inch cake.

title: quick tuna dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together except almonds and cheese. Sprinkle with almonds or cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: berry mallow yam bake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, oatmeal and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Lightly toss 1 cup of crumb mixture with yams and cranberries.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cover with marshmallows and broil until lightly browned.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar; beat eggs separately.
Sift flour once.
Mix eggs and flour gradually.
Add vanilla and lemon flavorings.
Mix well.
Grease and flour Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 275° to 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes to 2 hours (depending on oven).

title: ronco noodle ham casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook until tender. Stir in mushrooms and salt.
Blend soup and milk.

title: cherry crunch
directions: In 8 x 12-inch dish, smooth cherry pie filling, then pineapple, then sugar, cake mix, melted butter and pecans.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Bake the pie shell; cool.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in a medium saucepan.
Gradually stir in water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Gradually stir at least half the mixture into the egg yolks; blend into the hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Immediately pour into pie shell.
Prepare meringue (recipe to follow).

title: christmas strawberries
directions: Mix together; let stand 1 hour.
Take small portion, roll in strawberry jello crystals and shape like strawberries.
Stir in a cocktail toothpick.
Trim with green leaves of decorative frosting.

title: reese's chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating well.
Stir in chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes. (Do not overbake.)
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: grilled roast beef and swiss sandwiches
directions: Mix equal parts mayonnaise with spicy mustard or horseradish. Spread this mixture on inside of bread. Add meat and cheese. Butter outside of bread and grill as you would a grilled cheese sandwich.

title: no bake boston cream cake
directions: Make pudding according to directions on box.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer graham crackers on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread mixture over graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers, another layer of mixture, another layer of graham crackers.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Spread icing on top of graham crackers.
Eat!
Make 24 hours in advance and refrigerate.

title: skillet supper
directions: Put all in a big pot. Bring to simmer and cook for 15 minutes until rice is done. Serve topped with sour cream.

title: vada's congealed marshmallow salad
directions: Pour gelatin into boiling water; add marshmallows and stir well. Pour in large mold and refrigerate until almost firm. Thoroughly mix cream cheese with the sugar and the gelatin. Add lemon juice, salt, pineapple and nuts. Fold in prepared whipped cream or Dream Whip. Chill until firm.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onion and add garlic powder, beef and sausage.
Pour off grease. Stir in tomato puree, one can water, salt, pepper, basil and oregano.
Simmer until sauce thickens.
While sauce simmers, cook noodles following box instructions.
Drain and place in a bowl of cold water to keep from sticking together.
Drain noodles and arrange in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or two 1 1/2-quart baking dishes the noodles, sauce, Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle Parmesan.
Continue layering until dish is full.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: banana split cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick butter.
Press into the greased pan.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes and place in greased casserole.
Melt butter. Add other ingredients and cook until cheese is melted.
Pour sauce over potatoes and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetarian black beans
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat oil; add onoin, green pepper, celery, scallions and garlic.
Cook about 4 minutes, stirring occasionally until vegetables are softened.
Add tomato paste; cook and stir 2 minutes.
Add beans, broth, herbs and seasonings; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low, simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes until somewhat thickened.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place in a well oiled baking dish the potatoes (washed, peeled and thinly sliced).
Heat in small saucepan the milk, dry mustard, water and grated cheese.
Season with salt, pepper and the grated onion.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; continue baking until the potatoes are soft and tender and the top is brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzel sticks, sugar and margarine and spread into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 200° for 8 minutes and cool.
Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzels.
Seal the edge good.
Melt jello in water.
Add strawberries.
Pour over cream cheese to make top layer of salad.
Chill.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla, lemon juice and eggs. Beat well.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Sift together salt, flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Combine with banana mixture.
Add sour cream, nuts and chopped bananas.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until surface springs back when touched. Cool in pan on cake rack.
Put in plastic bags to mellow.
Freezes very well.

title: applesauce raisin bars
directions: Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder, salt and soda.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion and garlic slowly in oil for about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except chips and cheese and simmer for about 1/2 hour.
Serve topped with cheese and with chips.
Adjust the seasonings to taste.
You may want to add some of the chicken broth from the boiled chicken.

title: quick asparagus salad
directions: Cut or snap off tough ends of asparagus and cut off the small wedge-shaped leaves up to 2 inches from the tip.
Wash well and cut on the diagonal into 1 1/2-inch lengths.
Bring 6 cups of water to a boil in a saucepan over high heat.
Add the asparagus pieces.
As soon as the water returns to a boil, drain and quickly cool in cold water to stop the cooking.
Drain well.
Just before serving, place the asparagus in a serving bowl and toss with the soy sauce and sesame seed oil.
Serve at room temperature.

title: patsy's green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo; gradually add flour, water, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
Add beans and sour cream. Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and mushrooms.

Spread a thin layer of mixture on bottom of glass baking dish. Lay chicken on top. Cover chicken with remaining mixture. Sprinkle paprika on top (not necessary for taste). Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve on top of Lipton chicken rice.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix marshmallows and pineapple; let stand 6 to 8 hours.
Add cherries and nuts.
Just before serving, fold in 1 pint whipped cream and bananas.
Serve on angel food cake.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip.
Add other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados with fork.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Serve as a dip, or lettuce as a salad.

title: country apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla until well blended.
Beat in flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
When completely mixed (batter will be very thick), stir in nuts and apples. Spread batter evenly in prepared pan.
Bake about 35 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and garnish with nuts.

title: bicycle pork
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place in a large casserole.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Add onion.
Mix flour and milk together until flour is smooth.
Pour over potatoes and onion. Now dot this mixture with butter; place pork chops on top.
Salt and pepper to taste and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until potatoes are soft.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Wet loaf bread with water and mash.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Add enough water to start cooking without burning.
Stir often.
Cook until meat is done.
May add potatoes (chopped), if you like.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix all remaining ingredients; pour over butter.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes.

title: won ton's
directions: Saute meat in oil until brown and crumbly.
Add all ingredients; season with pepper and soy sauce to taste.
Drain off excess oil and cool.
Place one teaspoon of meat mixture in center of won ton square.
Fold diagonally and seal edges by wetting with a dab of water.
Deep-fry in 360° oil until won ton is golden. Serve hot with won ton sauce or mustard with soy sauce.

title: raisin salad
directions: Toss together the broccoli, cauliflower, raisins, onion and crumbled bacon. Then cover with mixture of salad dressing, vinegar, milk and sweetener. Toss gently to blend.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: cherry delight
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch dish with graham crackers.
Mix large box of pudding with milk and set aside 5 minutes.
Then add Cool Whip. Blend by hand.
Add pudding mix to dish, then another layer of graham crackers, then pudding; top with cherry filling.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Kids and adults love this.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Bring tea bags, sugar and water to a boil. Remove from heat and add cinnamon sticks and cloves. Let set for 30 minutes; then add Jell-O, cranberry juice, apple juice, orange juice and lemon juice. Heat and serve hot.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or lightly browned on top when toothpick inserted into center is clean.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix together carrots, onions and peppers.
Mix other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate for at least 12 hours.
This will keep for weeks in the refrigerator.

title: pommes de terre lyonnaise(sauteed potatoes with onions)
directions: Cook potatoes in their jackets in boiling water in a large saucepan for 20 minutes.
Drain, cool, peel and slice 1/4-inch thick. Heat butter and oil in a large skillet until the bubbling subsides.
Add potatoes and onions and cook until golden brown, about 10 minutes, turning gently 2 or 3 times.
Sprinkle potatoes with salt and pepper.

title: 3 minute peanut butter fudge
directions: Pour onto large plate or into a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet with lip.
Allow to set up.

title: chicken curry
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cook broccoli as directed on box. In separate bowl, mix together cream of mushroom soup, mayonnaise, curry powder, milk, salt and pepper; set aside.
Grease casserole (9 x 13-inch) dish.
Layer as follows:
chopped chicken, chopped broccoli, sauce mixture, grated cheese and croutons.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
May assemble up to croutons the night before.
Add croutons before baking.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Mix in heavy 2 qt. sauce pan, sugar, milk, marshmallows, butter and salt. Cook stirring constantly over medium heat to a full boil. Boil and stir for 5 minutes. Take off heat, stir in chocolate pieces and stir until completely melted. Add nuts and vanilla.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook and drain beef and sausage.
Add and melt tomato sauce, Velveeta cheese and pepperoncini.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.
(Jimmy Dean also has medium or mild sausage.) Put dip on some type of warmer.

title: brownie dessert
directions: Cut prepared brownies into bite size pieces.
In a glass bowl, layer half of the brownies, followed by half of the prepared pudding and half of the whipped topping.
Repeat layers, ending with the whipped topping.
Garnish top with chopped pecans, if desired.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: quiche
directions: Brown pie shell with Parmesan for about 15 minutes at 450°. Line pie shell with sliced tomato.
Saute squash, onion, green pepper and garlic salt.
Drain off excess margarine.
Place mixture in pie shell and top with the combined mixture of Mozzarella cheese and mayonnaise.
Place in a 400° oven for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 large loaf pans or 3 small.
Mix shortening and sugar in a large bowl. Add eggs, zucchini and water. Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and spices.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Blend in vanilla. Pour into pans. Bake 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Loosen sides and remove from pans.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs (not too stiff) in bowl.
Combine sugar and syrup; boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into beaten eggs (small amount at a time; otherwise, eggs will curdle).
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Cook in moderate oven at 350° to 375° until set, approximately 45 minutes.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients. Do not drain juice from pineapple. Pour into casserole dish and freeze.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.

title: amy's chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil chicken breasts until meat is white all the way through.
Cook mixed vegetables in microwave according to directions.
Let chicken cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Drain vegetables.
Mix chicken, vegetables and soup in large bowl.
Pour into deep dish crust.
Cover top with remaining crust and bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: congealed tomato dip
directions: Place bowl in refrigerator to congeal.

title: ham and macaroni bake
directions: Combine cooked macaroni with other ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup of the cheese.	Top with the Cheddar cheese and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Good way to use leftover ham.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Chop the cabbage, carrot and green pepper.
Mix in salt and put in 3-quart bowl.
Let stand for 1 hour; drain.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top casserole with 2 cups of corn flakes or 1 package of Ritz crackers and add 1/4 cup melted butter or margarine.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: custard corn casserole
directions: Mix the corn with the eggs that have been beaten lightly, set aside.

title: louisiana turnip greens with cornmeal dumplings
directions: Wash greens thoroughly. Cover with cold salted water and let soak 1 hour; drain.
Bring water to a boil; add greens and salt pork; return to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer about 1 hour or until greens are very tender.
Add salt to taste. Combine cornmeal, egg and milk.
Mix well.
Stir in shortening. Drop batter by teaspoonfuls on top of simmering greens.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes longer.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water, cool.
Add Kool-Aid, pineapple juice, and ginger ale.
Chill & pour over ice.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes and onion into eighths.
In a 3-quart saucepan, add green onions, garlic and butter.
Saute for 1 minute.
Fold in the potato and onion eighths, following with the chicken broth. Simmer on low heat for 20 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Puree cooked soup in food processor or blender until smooth.
Add cream, milk, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Can be served hot or cold.
Garnish with croutons, chipped chives and/or parsley.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Arrange caps on baking sheet. Chop stems and saute with onion and garlic in butter until tender. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Stuff each mushroom cap with mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and potato skillet(4 servings)
directions: In a 10-inch skillet brown ham in margarine and brown sugar. Remove ham; pour off drippings.
Mix in same skillet, soup, milk, water, onions, salt and pepper.
Stir in potatoes and carrots.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make 8 patties shaped like hamburgers.
Spray a nonstick pan with Pam and fry until crisp.

title: crock pot applebutter
directions: Cook apples before putting in crock pot. Cook on low in crock pot for 10 hours except last hour turn on high and with lid off.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Put into 3 loaf pans 1/2 full.
Bake for 60 minutes.
Use knife for test.
Bake at 325°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook spinach in saucepan according to package directions. Drain well, pressing spinach against colander to remove excess water. Return to pan; set aside. If you're using bacon drippings, add them to spinach at this point.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine soup, sour cream, and garlic salt. Add frozen potatoes and Cheddar cheese - Mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2 inch greased baking dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 55 - 60 minutes, till brown on top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs,
sugar,
salt,
oleo and corn syrup.
Add pecan halves and vanilla.
Bake at 450° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and baking soda.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add first mixture to second and bake at 375° in a 9 x 12-inch greased loaf pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour.
Beat eggs slightly; add to dry mixture.
Add softened margarine.
Mix well.
Add syrup, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: slop
directions: In a large pan brown ground beef over medium heat.
Tear tortillas into bite-size pieces and add enough to soak up grease and make tortillas soft.
Add soup and milk, stir until just mixed.
Add corn and stir. May add green chilies or serve on the side.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese and heat until melts. Serve.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar.
Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add confectioners sugar until right consistency to spread.
Easy.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Trim broccoli and chop in chunks.
Microwave until tender. Cool slightly; use the water to chop up broccoli in blender.
In saucepan, add to broccoli-water mixture, the soup, cream and spices.
Heat slowly to simmer; a wire whisk helps to get it smooth.

title: sesame knots
directions: Separate dough and loosely tie each piece of dough into a knot.
Arrange rolls 1-inch apart on an ungreased baking sheet. Brush with butter. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 10 servings.

title: garlic cheese log
directions: Soften cheeses to room temperature.
Mix well and shape into logs and roll in mixture of chili powder and paprika.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cover chicken breasts with water and par boil until tender, about 35 minutes.
Thaw broccoli and drain.
Arrange broccoli in a greased casserole (9 x 12-inch).
Top with chicken cut into strips.
Mix together soup, lemon juice, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs or Ritz cracker crumbs.
Place on top and sprinkle cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: crab squares
directions: Combine all ingredients, except muffins.
Spread on muffin halves.
Freeze, which makes easier to cut into pinwheel pieces. Broil until browned on top, approximately 8 minutes.

title: casey's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (convection oven 300°).
Mix flour, baking soda and salt in bowl.
In a mixing bowl or food processor, mix sugars, vanilla and margarine.
Mix well and add eggs.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture and mix well.
Stir in nuts (coarsely chopped) and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart onto cookie pan covered with parchment paper.
Bake 8 minutes until edges of cookies are golden.
Remove with spatula and cool on rack.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Place in double boiler and melt.
Cook until it thickens. Make a 9-inch pie shell.
Use a graham cracker crust recipe, substituting crackers with vanilla wafers.
Fill with vanilla ice cream.
Top with chocolate mixture.
Cover with chopped pecans. Freeze until 5 minutes before serving.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix noodles, half of sausage, the spaghetti and pizza sauces, mushrooms, Cheddar cheese and half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Put into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle with pepperoni.
Sprinkle with remaining sausage and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: raisin cake
directions: Melt margarine or butter with raisins while hot.
Mix flour, cocoa, soda and spices together with eggs and add to raisins. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until well done.
(Do not use a mixer, stir with spoon only.)

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all above ingredients, except crackers and margarine. Place in large casserole.
Make crumbs of crackers and spread on casserole.
Top with sliced margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Add vanilla, chopped nuts and coconut to mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 layers.

title: stuffed flank steak and gravy
directions: Unfold steak and pound between sheets of waxed paper until uniformly 1/2-inch thick.
Put onion, water, celery and butter in Dutch oven and simmer over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add stuffing mix and stir until moistened.
Spoon stuffing down middle of steak. Bring up long sides to cover stuffing and either skewer it or tie it.
Tuck in short ends.
In a clean pot, add olive oil and heat. Cook steak 10 minutes, turning with tongs to brown all sides.
Add broth, bay leaves and marjoram and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover; simmer.
Turn steak every 30 minutes until fork-tender. Take steak out and keep warm.
Discard bay leaves.
Boil liquid and stir in flour mix.
Whisk until smooth and let thicken.
Serve gravy with meat or pour over meat on platter.
Delicious and very popular with guests.
May also be cooked in the oven in a covered roasting pan.

title: curry pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients and add to drippings.
Pour over pork chops.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish and bake covered at 325° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake for an additional 45 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar with butter.
Mix 1 cup sugar with eggs and lemon juice.
Combine the mixtures and pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: marge's chocolate syrup
directions: Melt chocolate. Add butter and blend. Add water and slowly bring to boil. (Be careful not to burn.) Add sugar and corn syrup. Boil 4 to 5 minutes. Add vanilla and salt. Serve immediately over vanilla ice cream or let cool a bit first.

title: tuna salad(makes 4 to 6 sandwiches)
directions: Flake tuna.
Add boiled eggs, apple, pickles, salt and pepper. Mix with enough salad dressing to hold salad together.
Use on sandwiches or place in lettuce cups for salads.
Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients together in a large bowl. Mix last four dressing ingredients together with a whisk and pour over cabbage mix.

title: chicken scaloppine
directions: Remove fat from chicken and flatten by slapping with palm of your hand.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and oregano.
Add a little salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until foamy and dip chicken in it.
Coat chicken with bread crumbs and dip again in egg whites. Coat with bread crumbs a second time.
Heat oil in a nonstick skillet and brown chicken on both sides.
Reduce heat.
Add wine and cover.
Cook 5 more minutes.
There will be no wine left in pan.
Serve with pasta.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer graham crackers, filling, crackers, filling and crackers.
Frost and refrigerate overnight.
Use at least a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Cook rice in 1 tablespoon of oil until light brown.
Put in square casserole and stir in chicken broth.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add more broth if rice dries.
Cook chicken strips in 2 tablespoons of oil; cook and stir until chicken is white.
Add celery, onion, green pepper and soy sauce.

title: baked chicken and lentils
directions: In 3-quart casserole, combine the carrot slices, onion, lentils, bouillon granules, bay leaves, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Add hot water and stir gently to mix.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all together and fold in one 9 ounce Cool Whip.
Pour into a graham cracker pie shell and freeze.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and onion in margarine; drain. Add remaining ingredients and cook on low for 2 hours.

title: country style steak
directions: Put steak in crock-pot.
Mix gravy mixes according to package. Pour over steak.
Cook on high for 1 to 2 hours.
Then on low for 5 to 6 hours.
I cook mine at night.

title: cajun chicken(low calorie)
directions: Combine dry seasonings in a large plastic bag.
Place chicken in bag, one piece at a time, and shake until well coated.

title: nancy's scalloped corn
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, salt and cold milk.
Add scalded milk while stirring.
Stir constantly.
Cook on low heat until thick. Add beaten egg yolks, then cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from stove; add coconut flavor.
Cover top with meringue made of 3 egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar.
Brown in oven.

title: swedish butter cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour and mix.
Divide in half and make 2 logs out of dough.
Place each on wax paper and sprinkle with colored sugar or nuts.
Roll logs over sugar or nuts so it is covered on the outside.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate until hard enough to slice.
Slice medium to thick and bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until done.

title: apple squares
directions: Soften margarine.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Gradually add flour.
Spread 3/4 of batter in a greased and floured 10-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over batter.
Dab remaining batter over filling, pulling it together but letting some of the filling show.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until golden.

title: canadian bars
directions: Mix together cocoa, 1/2 cup butter and sugar; beat over boiling water until butter melts.
Add graham crackers, crushed coconut and nuts.
Pat mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1/4 cup butter, milk, pudding mix and powdered sugar.
Cover first layer with pudding mixture.
Let cool in refrigerator 15 minutes, then spread with 4 squares semi-sweet chocolate and 1 tablespoon melted butter (1 package chocolate chips may be used).

title: yellow coconut dream cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together and bake in greased and floured angel food or Bundt cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cut butter into flour until it resembles coarse crumbs. Add flavorings and cheese.
Roll into 1-inch balls and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 50 to 60 puffs.

title: fun face paint
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in bowl until smooth.
Add glycerine, blending until creamy.
Blend in food coloring 1 drop at a time until desired shade of color is reached.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups, oleo, mushrooms and milk.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread rice.
Pour 2/3 of soup mixture over rice and gently stir.
Lay chicken on soup-rice mixture and pour rest of soup mixture over.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until lightly brown on top.

title: garlic bread
directions: Spread each side of bread generously with butter.
Sprinkle with seasoning to your preference.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until crispy.

title: pull apart rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan well and sprinkle bottom of pan with nuts. Place frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with pudding.
Mix brown sugar and butter and sprinkle over tops of rolls.
Top with cinnamon.
Set pan in cold oven overnight.
Take out in morning and preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian candied sweet potatoes
directions: Use fresh sweet potatoes.
Boil potatoes, cool and peel.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and water; cook about 10 minutes.
Add margarine and pineapple to syrup.
Pour over potatoes in baking dish, which have been sliced.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Freezes well, before cooking, if desired, to use later.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Saute onions and garlic in salad oil in skillet.
Combine bread and milk and blend together.
Add garlic, onions, beef, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Blend together by hand.
Pass mixture through grinder.
Add parsley and eggs.
Form the meat balls by hand and put on sheet pans, greased.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until done.

title: hobo bread
directions: Combine currants and soda.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over. Let cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into cans that have been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350°.
When dough rises to top of the can, test with toothpick for doneness.

title: baked turbot fillets
directions: Cut fish into 6 portions.
Place in greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Brush fish with oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake at 350° about 20 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: eggnog
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks and add sugar.
Add milk.
Beat egg whites until they stand in peaks.
Add to milk mixture.
Beat cream until frothy.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Chill.
Add vanilla and nutmeg, if desired.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Remove edges of bread and cube.
Add all ingredients together in a lightly greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes the next morning.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple in bottom of casserole dish. Mix sugar and flour; put on top of pineapple. Add grated cheese. Mix crushed crackers and melted margarine together and add to top. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil mixture of last 4 ingredients on stove for 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of baking soda and mix well.
Pour over popcorn in greased grocery bag*.
Shake well and microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake well and microwave for 1/2 minute longer.
Pour out of bag and cool.

title: macaroni cheese
directions: Drain macaroni. Combine with eggs, cheese and milk.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish sprayed with Pam.
Cook in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not cook on real high heat.
If you do, the macaroni will boil and not be as good.

title: hot chicken supreme
directions: Remove chicken from bones and skin. Cut into small pieces. Mix chicken with next 12 ingredients. Pour into 13 x 9 casserole dish; top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle onion rings over top. Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: rum balls
directions: Crush wafers in blender; chop pecans finely.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and shape into small balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar or cocoa and store in airtight container at least a week before using.
Makes 50.

title: vegetable christmas tree
directions: You will also need a 12 to 18-inch styrofoam cone and colored foil or wrapping paper.

title: corn meal dressing
directions: *Follow recipe on bag but double recipe.

title: crumb crust
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine until particles are fine.
Press into the bottom and sides of pie plate or 8-inch square dish.
Reserve small amount to sprinkle on top of pie.

title: best ever chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs until well blended.
Add salt.
Stir in flour and add chocolate syrup, vanilla and nuts. Pour mixture into 9-inch square pan. Smooth top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into squares.

title: my favorite chocolate pie
directions: Never put the yolk of the egg in it, makes it lumpy.
